62 namespace {
63  class UnqualUsingEntry {
64  const DeclContext *Nominated;
65  const DeclContext *CommonAncestor;
66 
67  public:
68  UnqualUsingEntry(const DeclContext *Nominated,
69  const DeclContext *CommonAncestor)
70  : Nominated(Nominated), CommonAncestor(CommonAncestor) {
71  }
72 
73  const DeclContext *getCommonAncestor() const {
74  return CommonAncestor;
75  }
76 
77  const DeclContext *getNominatedNamespace() const {
78  return Nominated;
79  }
80 
81  // Sort by the pointer value of the common ancestor.
82  struct Comparator {
83  bool operator()(const UnqualUsingEntry &L, const UnqualUsingEntry &R) {
84  return L.getCommonAncestor() < R.getCommonAncestor();
85  }
86 
87  bool operator()(const UnqualUsingEntry &E, const DeclContext *DC) {
88  return E.getCommonAncestor() < DC;
89  }
90 
91  bool operator()(const DeclContext *DC, const UnqualUsingEntry &E) {
92  return DC < E.getCommonAncestor();
93  }
94  };
95  };

97  /// A collection of using directives, as used by C++ unqualified
98  /// lookup.
99  class UnqualUsingDirectiveSet {
100  Sema &SemaRef;
101 
102  typedef SmallVector<UnqualUsingEntry, 8> ListTy;
103 
104  ListTy list;
105  llvm::SmallPtrSet<DeclContext*, 8> visited;
106 
107  public:
108  UnqualUsingDirectiveSet(Sema &SemaRef) : SemaRef(SemaRef) {}
109 
110  void visitScopeChain(Scope *S, Scope *InnermostFileScope) {
111  // C++ [namespace.udir]p1:
112  // During unqualified name lookup, the names appear as if they
113  // were declared in the nearest enclosing namespace which contains
114  // both the using-directive and the nominated namespace.
115  DeclContext *InnermostFileDC = InnermostFileScope->getEntity();
116  assert(InnermostFileDC && InnermostFileDC->isFileContext());
117 
118  for (; S; S = S->getParent()) {
119  // C++ [namespace.udir]p1:
120  // A using-directive shall not appear in class scope, but may
121  // appear in namespace scope or in block scope.
122  DeclContext *Ctx = S->getEntity();
123  if (Ctx && Ctx->isFileContext()) {
124  visit(Ctx, Ctx);
125  } else if (!Ctx || Ctx->isFunctionOrMethod()) {
126  for (auto *I : S->using_directives())
127  if (SemaRef.isVisible(I))
128  visit(I, InnermostFileDC);
129  }
130  }
131  }
132 
133  // Visits a context and collect all of its using directives
134  // recursively. Treats all using directives as if they were
135  // declared in the context.
136  //
137  // A given context is only every visited once, so it is important
138  // that contexts be visited from the inside out in order to get
139  // the effective DCs right.
140  void visit(DeclContext *DC, DeclContext *EffectiveDC) {
141  if (!visited.insert(DC).second)
142  return;
143 
144  addUsingDirectives(DC, EffectiveDC);
145  }
146 
147  // Visits a using directive and collects all of its using
148  // directives recursively. Treats all using directives as if they
149  // were declared in the effective DC.
150  void visit(UsingDirectiveDecl *UD, DeclContext *EffectiveDC) {
151  DeclContext *NS = UD->getNominatedNamespace();
152  if (!visited.insert(NS).second)
153  return;
154 
155  addUsingDirective(UD, EffectiveDC);
156  addUsingDirectives(NS, EffectiveDC);
157  }
158 
159  // Adds all the using directives in a context (and those nominated
160  // by its using directives, transitively) as if they appeared in
161  // the given effective context.
162  void addUsingDirectives(DeclContext *DC, DeclContext *EffectiveDC) {
163  SmallVector<DeclContext*, 4> queue;
164  while (true) {
165  for (auto *UD : DC->using_directives()) {
166  DeclContext *NS = UD->getNominatedNamespace();
167  if (SemaRef.isVisible(UD) && visited.insert(NS).second) {
168  addUsingDirective(UD, EffectiveDC);
169  queue.push_back(NS);
170  }
171  }
172 
173  if (queue.empty())
174  return;
175 
176  DC = queue.pop_back_val();
177  }
178  }
179 
180  // Add a using directive as if it had been declared in the given
181  // context. This helps implement C++ [namespace.udir]p3:
182  // The using-directive is transitive: if a scope contains a
183  // using-directive that nominates a second namespace that itself
184  // contains using-directives, the effect is as if the
185  // using-directives from the second namespace also appeared in
186  // the first.
187  void addUsingDirective(UsingDirectiveDecl *UD, DeclContext *EffectiveDC) {
188  // Find the common ancestor between the effective context and
189  // the nominated namespace.
190  DeclContext *Common = UD->getNominatedNamespace();
191  while (!Common->Encloses(EffectiveDC))
192  Common = Common->getParent();
193  Common = Common->getPrimaryContext();
194 
195  list.push_back(UnqualUsingEntry(UD->getNominatedNamespace(), Common));
196  }
197 
198  void done() { llvm::sort(list, UnqualUsingEntry::Comparator()); }
199 
200  typedef ListTy::const_iterator const_iterator;
201 
202  const_iterator begin() const { return list.begin(); }
203  const_iterator end() const { return list.end(); }
204 
205  llvm::iterator_range<const_iterator>
206  getNamespacesFor(const DeclContext *DC) const {
207  return llvm::make_range(std::equal_range(begin(), end(),
208  DC->getPrimaryContext(),
209  UnqualUsingEntry::Comparator()));
210  }
211  };
212 } // end anonymous namespace
213 
214 // Retrieve the set of identifier namespaces that correspond to a
215 // specific kind of name lookup.
216 static inline unsigned getIDNS(Sema::LookupNameKind NameKind,
217  bool CPlusPlus,
218  bool Redeclaration) {
219  unsigned IDNS = 0;
220  switch (NameKind) {
221  case Sema::LookupObjCImplicitSelfParam:
222  case Sema::LookupOrdinaryName:
223  case Sema::LookupRedeclarationWithLinkage:
224  case Sema::LookupLocalFriendName:
225  case Sema::LookupDestructorName:
226  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Ordinary;
227  if (CPlusPlus) {
228  IDNS |= Decl::IDNS_Tag | Decl::IDNS_Member | Decl::IDNS_Namespace;
229  if (Redeclaration)
230  IDNS |= Decl::IDNS_TagFriend | Decl::IDNS_OrdinaryFriend;
231  }
232  if (Redeclaration)
233  IDNS |= Decl::IDNS_LocalExtern;
234  break;
235 
236  case Sema::LookupOperatorName:
237  // Operator lookup is its own crazy thing; it is not the same
238  // as (e.g.) looking up an operator name for redeclaration.
239  assert(!Redeclaration && "cannot do redeclaration operator lookup");
240  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_NonMemberOperator;
241  break;
242 
243  case Sema::LookupTagName:
244  if (CPlusPlus) {
245  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Type;
246 
247  // When looking for a redeclaration of a tag name, we add:
248  // 1) TagFriend to find undeclared friend decls
249  // 2) Namespace because they can't "overload" with tag decls.
250  // 3) Tag because it includes class templates, which can't
251  // "overload" with tag decls.
252  if (Redeclaration)
253  IDNS |= Decl::IDNS_Tag | Decl::IDNS_TagFriend | Decl::IDNS_Namespace;
254  } else {
255  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Tag;
256  }
257  break;
258 
259  case Sema::LookupLabel:
260  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Label;
261  break;
262 
263  case Sema::LookupMemberName:
264  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Member;
265  if (CPlusPlus)
266  IDNS |= Decl::IDNS_Tag | Decl::IDNS_Ordinary;
267  break;
268 
269  case Sema::LookupNestedNameSpecifierName:
270  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Type | Decl::IDNS_Namespace;
271  break;
272 
273  case Sema::LookupNamespaceName:
274  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Namespace;
275  break;
276 
277  case Sema::LookupUsingDeclName:
278  assert(Redeclaration && "should only be used for redecl lookup");
279  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Ordinary | Decl::IDNS_Tag | Decl::IDNS_Member |
280  Decl::IDNS_Using | Decl::IDNS_TagFriend | Decl::IDNS_OrdinaryFriend |
281  Decl::IDNS_LocalExtern;
282  break;
283 
284  case Sema::LookupObjCProtocolName:
285  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_ObjCProtocol;
286  break;
287 
288  case Sema::LookupOMPReductionName:
289  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_OMPReduction;
290  break;
291 
292  case Sema::LookupOMPMapperName:
293  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_OMPMapper;
294  break;
295 
296  case Sema::LookupAnyName:
297  IDNS = Decl::IDNS_Ordinary | Decl::IDNS_Tag | Decl::IDNS_Member
298  | Decl::IDNS_Using | Decl::IDNS_Namespace | Decl::IDNS_ObjCProtocol
299  | Decl::IDNS_Type;
300  break;
301  }
302  return IDNS;
303 }
304 
305 void LookupResult::configure() {
306  IDNS = getIDNS(LookupKind, getSema().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus,
307  isForRedeclaration());
308 
309  // If we're looking for one of the allocation or deallocation
310  // operators, make sure that the implicitly-declared new and delete
311  // operators can be found.
312  switch (NameInfo.getName().getCXXOverloadedOperator()) {
313  case OO_New:
314  case OO_Delete:
315  case OO_Array_New:
316  case OO_Array_Delete:
317  getSema().DeclareGlobalNewDelete();
318  break;
319 
320  default:
321  break;
322  }
323 
324  // Compiler builtins are always visible, regardless of where they end
325  // up being declared.
326  if (IdentifierInfo *Id = NameInfo.getName().getAsIdentifierInfo()) {
327  if (unsigned BuiltinID = Id->getBuiltinID()) {
328  if (!getSema().Context.BuiltinInfo.isPredefinedLibFunction(BuiltinID))
329  AllowHidden = true;
330  }
331  }
332 }
333 
334 bool LookupResult::checkDebugAssumptions() const {
335  // This function is never called by NDEBUG builds.
336  assert(ResultKind != NotFound || Decls.size() == 0);
337  assert(ResultKind != Found || Decls.size() == 1);
338  assert(ResultKind != FoundOverloaded || Decls.size() > 1 ||
339  (Decls.size() == 1 &&
340  isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>((*begin())->getUnderlyingDecl())));
341  assert(ResultKind != FoundUnresolvedValue || checkUnresolved());
342  assert(ResultKind != Ambiguous || Decls.size() > 1 ||
343  (Decls.size() == 1 && (Ambiguity == AmbiguousBaseSubobjects ||
344  Ambiguity == AmbiguousBaseSubobjectTypes)));
345  assert((Paths != nullptr) == (ResultKind == Ambiguous &&
346  (Ambiguity == AmbiguousBaseSubobjectTypes ||
347  Ambiguity == AmbiguousBaseSubobjects)));
348  return true;
349 }

351 // Necessary because CXXBasePaths is not complete in Sema.h
352 void LookupResult::deletePaths(CXXBasePaths *Paths) {
353  delete Paths;
354 }

356 /// Get a representative context for a declaration such that two declarations
357 /// will have the same context if they were found within the same scope.
358 static const DeclContext *getContextForScopeMatching(const Decl *D) {
359  // For function-local declarations, use that function as the context. This
360  // doesn't account for scopes within the function; the caller must deal with
361  // those.
362  if (const DeclContext *DC = D->getLexicalDeclContext();
363  DC->isFunctionOrMethod())
364  return DC;
365 
366  // Otherwise, look at the semantic context of the declaration. The
367  // declaration must have been found there.
368  return D->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext();
369 }
370 
371 /// Determine whether \p D is a better lookup result than \p Existing,
372 /// given that they declare the same entity.
373 static bool isPreferredLookupResult(Sema &S, Sema::LookupNameKind Kind,
374  const NamedDecl *D,
375  const NamedDecl *Existing) {
376  // When looking up redeclarations of a using declaration, prefer a using
377  // shadow declaration over any other declaration of the same entity.
378  if (Kind == Sema::LookupUsingDeclName && isa<UsingShadowDecl>(D) &&
379  !isa<UsingShadowDecl>(Existing))
380  return true;
381 
382  const auto *DUnderlying = D->getUnderlyingDecl();
383  const auto *EUnderlying = Existing->getUnderlyingDecl();
384 
385  // If they have different underlying declarations, prefer a typedef over the
386  // original type (this happens when two type declarations denote the same
387  // type), per a generous reading of C++ [dcl.typedef]p3 and p4. The typedef
388  // might carry additional semantic information, such as an alignment override.
389  // However, per C++ [dcl.typedef]p5, when looking up a tag name, prefer a tag
390  // declaration over a typedef. Also prefer a tag over a typedef for
391  // destructor name lookup because in some contexts we only accept a
392  // class-name in a destructor declaration.
393  if (DUnderlying->getCanonicalDecl() != EUnderlying->getCanonicalDecl()) {
394  assert(isa<TypeDecl>(DUnderlying) && isa<TypeDecl>(EUnderlying));
395  bool HaveTag = isa<TagDecl>(EUnderlying);
396  bool WantTag =
397  Kind == Sema::LookupTagName || Kind == Sema::LookupDestructorName;
398  return HaveTag != WantTag;
399  }
400 
401  // Pick the function with more default arguments.
402  // FIXME: In the presence of ambiguous default arguments, we should keep both,
403  // so we can diagnose the ambiguity if the default argument is needed.
404  // See C++ [over.match.best]p3.
405  if (const auto *DFD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(DUnderlying)) {
406  const auto *EFD = cast<FunctionDecl>(EUnderlying);
407  unsigned DMin = DFD->getMinRequiredArguments();
408  unsigned EMin = EFD->getMinRequiredArguments();
409  // If D has more default arguments, it is preferred.
410  if (DMin != EMin)
411  return DMin < EMin;
412  // FIXME: When we track visibility for default function arguments, check
413  // that we pick the declaration with more visible default arguments.
414  }
415 
416  // Pick the template with more default template arguments.
417  if (const auto *DTD = dyn_cast<TemplateDecl>(DUnderlying)) {
418  const auto *ETD = cast<TemplateDecl>(EUnderlying);
419  unsigned DMin = DTD->getTemplateParameters()->getMinRequiredArguments();
420  unsigned EMin = ETD->getTemplateParameters()->getMinRequiredArguments();
421  // If D has more default arguments, it is preferred. Note that default
422  // arguments (and their visibility) is monotonically increasing across the
423  // redeclaration chain, so this is a quick proxy for "is more recent".
424  if (DMin != EMin)
425  return DMin < EMin;
426  // If D has more *visible* default arguments, it is preferred. Note, an
427  // earlier default argument being visible does not imply that a later
428  // default argument is visible, so we can't just check the first one.
429  for (unsigned I = DMin, N = DTD->getTemplateParameters()->size();
430  I != N; ++I) {
431  if (!S.hasVisibleDefaultArgument(
432  ETD->getTemplateParameters()->getParam(I)) &&
433  S.hasVisibleDefaultArgument(
434  DTD->getTemplateParameters()->getParam(I)))
435  return true;
436  }
437  }
438 
439  // VarDecl can have incomplete array types, prefer the one with more complete
440  // array type.
441  if (const auto *DVD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(DUnderlying)) {
442  const auto *EVD = cast<VarDecl>(EUnderlying);
443  if (EVD->getType()->isIncompleteType() &&
444  !DVD->getType()->isIncompleteType()) {
445  // Prefer the decl with a more complete type if visible.
446  return S.isVisible(DVD);
447  }
448  return false; // Avoid picking up a newer decl, just because it was newer.
449  }
450 
451  // For most kinds of declaration, it doesn't really matter which one we pick.
452  if (!isa<FunctionDecl>(DUnderlying) && !isa<VarDecl>(DUnderlying)) {
453  // If the existing declaration is hidden, prefer the new one. Otherwise,
454  // keep what we've got.
455  return !S.isVisible(Existing);
456  }
457 
458  // Pick the newer declaration; it might have a more precise type.
459  for (const Decl *Prev = DUnderlying->getPreviousDecl(); Prev;
460  Prev = Prev->getPreviousDecl())
461  if (Prev == EUnderlying)
462  return true;
463  return false;
464 }
465 
466 /// Determine whether \p D can hide a tag declaration.
467 static bool canHideTag(const NamedDecl *D) {
468  // C++ [basic.scope.declarative]p4:
469  // Given a set of declarations in a single declarative region [...]
470  // exactly one declaration shall declare a class name or enumeration name
471  // that is not a typedef name and the other declarations shall all refer to
472  // the same variable, non-static data member, or enumerator, or all refer
473  // to functions and function templates; in this case the class name or
474  // enumeration name is hidden.
475  // C++ [basic.scope.hiding]p2:
476  // A class name or enumeration name can be hidden by the name of a
477  // variable, data member, function, or enumerator declared in the same
478  // scope.
479  // An UnresolvedUsingValueDecl always instantiates to one of these.
480  D = D->getUnderlyingDecl();
481  return isa<VarDecl>(D) || isa<EnumConstantDecl>(D) || isa<FunctionDecl>(D) ||
482  isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D) || isa<FieldDecl>(D) ||
483  isa<UnresolvedUsingValueDecl>(D);
484 }
485 
486 /// Resolves the result kind of this lookup.
487 void LookupResult::resolveKind() {
488  unsigned N = Decls.size();
489 
490  // Fast case: no possible ambiguity.
491  if (N == 0) {
492  assert(ResultKind == NotFound ||
493  ResultKind == NotFoundInCurrentInstantiation);
494  return;
495  }
496 
497  // If there's a single decl, we need to examine it to decide what
498  // kind of lookup this is.
499  if (N == 1) {
500  const NamedDecl *D = (*Decls.begin())->getUnderlyingDecl();
501  if (isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D))
502  ResultKind = FoundOverloaded;
503  else if (isa<UnresolvedUsingValueDecl>(D))
504  ResultKind = FoundUnresolvedValue;
505  return;
506  }
507 
508  // Don't do any extra resolution if we've already resolved as ambiguous.
509  if (ResultKind == Ambiguous) return;
510 
511  llvm::SmallDenseMap<const NamedDecl *, unsigned, 16> Unique;
512  llvm::SmallDenseMap<QualType, unsigned, 16> UniqueTypes;
513 
514  bool Ambiguous = false;
515  bool ReferenceToPlaceHolderVariable = false;
516  bool HasTag = false, HasFunction = false;
517  bool HasFunctionTemplate = false, HasUnresolved = false;
518  const NamedDecl *HasNonFunction = nullptr;
519 
520  llvm::SmallVector<const NamedDecl *, 4> EquivalentNonFunctions;
521  llvm::BitVector RemovedDecls(N);
522 
523  for (unsigned I = 0; I < N; I++) {
524  const NamedDecl *D = Decls[I]->getUnderlyingDecl();
525  D = cast<NamedDecl>(D->getCanonicalDecl());
526 
527  // Ignore an invalid declaration unless it's the only one left.
528  // Also ignore HLSLBufferDecl which not have name conflict with other Decls.
529  if ((D->isInvalidDecl() || isa<HLSLBufferDecl>(D)) &&
530  N - RemovedDecls.count() > 1) {
531  RemovedDecls.set(I);
532  continue;
533  }
534 
535  // C++ [basic.scope.hiding]p2:
536  // A class name or enumeration name can be hidden by the name of
537  // an object, function, or enumerator declared in the same
538  // scope. If a class or enumeration name and an object, function,
539  // or enumerator are declared in the same scope (in any order)
540  // with the same name, the class or enumeration name is hidden
541  // wherever the object, function, or enumerator name is visible.
542  if (HideTags && isa<TagDecl>(D)) {
543  bool Hidden = false;
544  for (auto *OtherDecl : Decls) {
545  if (canHideTag(OtherDecl) && !OtherDecl->isInvalidDecl() &&
546  getContextForScopeMatching(OtherDecl)->Equals(
547  getContextForScopeMatching(Decls[I]))) {
548  RemovedDecls.set(I);
549  Hidden = true;
550  break;
551  }
552  }
553  if (Hidden)
554  continue;
555  }
556 
557  std::optional<unsigned> ExistingI;
558 
559  // Redeclarations of types via typedef can occur both within a scope
560  // and, through using declarations and directives, across scopes. There is
561  // no ambiguity if they all refer to the same type, so unique based on the
562  // canonical type.
563  if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypeDecl>(D)) {
564  QualType T = getSema().Context.getTypeDeclType(TD);
565  auto UniqueResult = UniqueTypes.insert(
566  std::make_pair(getSema().Context.getCanonicalType(T), I));
567  if (!UniqueResult.second) {
568  // The type is not unique.
569  ExistingI = UniqueResult.first->second;
570  }
571  }
572 
573  // For non-type declarations, check for a prior lookup result naming this
574  // canonical declaration.
575  if (!D->isPlaceholderVar(getSema().getLangOpts()) && !ExistingI) {
576  auto UniqueResult = Unique.insert(std::make_pair(D, I));
577  if (!UniqueResult.second) {
578  // We've seen this entity before.
579  ExistingI = UniqueResult.first->second;
580  }
581  }
582 
583  if (ExistingI) {
584  // This is not a unique lookup result. Pick one of the results and
585  // discard the other.
586  if (isPreferredLookupResult(getSema(), getLookupKind(), Decls[I],
587  Decls[*ExistingI]))
588  Decls[*ExistingI] = Decls[I];
589  RemovedDecls.set(I);
590  continue;
591  }
592 
593  // Otherwise, do some decl type analysis and then continue.
594 
595  if (isa<UnresolvedUsingValueDecl>(D)) {
596  HasUnresolved = true;
597  } else if (isa<TagDecl>(D)) {
598  if (HasTag)
599  Ambiguous = true;
600  HasTag = true;
601  } else if (isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D)) {
602  HasFunction = true;
603  HasFunctionTemplate = true;
604  } else if (isa<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
605  HasFunction = true;
606  } else {
607  if (HasNonFunction) {
608  // If we're about to create an ambiguity between two declarations that
609  // are equivalent, but one is an internal linkage declaration from one
610  // module and the other is an internal linkage declaration from another
611  // module, just skip it.
612  if (getSema().isEquivalentInternalLinkageDeclaration(HasNonFunction,
613  D)) {
614  EquivalentNonFunctions.push_back(D);
615  RemovedDecls.set(I);
616  continue;
617  }
618  if (D->isPlaceholderVar(getSema().getLangOpts()) &&
619  getContextForScopeMatching(D) ==
620  getContextForScopeMatching(Decls[I])) {
621  ReferenceToPlaceHolderVariable = true;
622  }
623  Ambiguous = true;
624  }
625  HasNonFunction = D;
626  }
627  }
628 
629  // FIXME: This diagnostic should really be delayed until we're done with
630  // the lookup result, in case the ambiguity is resolved by the caller.
631  if (!EquivalentNonFunctions.empty() && !Ambiguous)
632  getSema().diagnoseEquivalentInternalLinkageDeclarations(
633  getNameLoc(), HasNonFunction, EquivalentNonFunctions);
634 
635  // Remove decls by replacing them with decls from the end (which
636  // means that we need to iterate from the end) and then truncating
637  // to the new size.
638  for (int I = RemovedDecls.find_last(); I >= 0; I = RemovedDecls.find_prev(I))
639  Decls[I] = Decls[--N];
640  Decls.truncate(N);
641 
642  if ((HasNonFunction && (HasFunction || HasUnresolved)) ||
643  (HideTags && HasTag && (HasFunction || HasNonFunction || HasUnresolved)))
644  Ambiguous = true;
645 
646  if (Ambiguous && ReferenceToPlaceHolderVariable)
647  setAmbiguous(LookupResult::AmbiguousReferenceToPlaceholderVariable);
648  else if (Ambiguous)
649  setAmbiguous(LookupResult::AmbiguousReference);
650  else if (HasUnresolved)
651  ResultKind = LookupResult::FoundUnresolvedValue;
652  else if (N > 1 || HasFunctionTemplate)
653  ResultKind = LookupResult::FoundOverloaded;
654  else
655  ResultKind = LookupResult::Found;
656 }
657 
658 void LookupResult::addDeclsFromBasePaths(const CXXBasePaths &P) {
659  CXXBasePaths::const_paths_iterator I, E;
660  for (I = P.begin(), E = P.end(); I != E; ++I)
661  for (DeclContext::lookup_iterator DI = I->Decls, DE = DI.end(); DI != DE;
662  ++DI)
663  addDecl(*DI);
664 }
665 
666 void LookupResult::setAmbiguousBaseSubobjects(CXXBasePaths &P) {
667  Paths = new CXXBasePaths;
668  Paths->swap(P);
669  addDeclsFromBasePaths(*Paths);
670  resolveKind();
671  setAmbiguous(AmbiguousBaseSubobjects);
672 }
673 
674 void LookupResult::setAmbiguousBaseSubobjectTypes(CXXBasePaths &P) {
675  Paths = new CXXBasePaths;
676  Paths->swap(P);
677  addDeclsFromBasePaths(*Paths);
678  resolveKind();
679  setAmbiguous(AmbiguousBaseSubobjectTypes);
680 }
681 
682 void LookupResult::print(raw_ostream &Out) {
683  Out << Decls.size() << " result(s)";
684  if (isAmbiguous()) Out << ", ambiguous";
685  if (Paths) Out << ", base paths present";
686 
687  for (iterator I = begin(), E = end(); I != E; ++I) {
688  Out << "\n";
689  (*I)->print(Out, 2);
690  }
691 }

693 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void LookupResult::dump() {
694  llvm::errs() << "lookup results for " << getLookupName().getAsString()
695  << ":\n";
696  for (NamedDecl *D : *this)
697  D->dump();
698 }

712 /// Lookup an OpenCL enum type.
713 static QualType getOpenCLEnumType(Sema &S, llvm::StringRef Name) {
714  LookupResult Result(S, &S.Context.Idents.get(Name), SourceLocation(),
715  Sema::LookupTagName);
716  S.LookupName(Result, S.TUScope);
717  if (Result.empty())

738 /// Get the QualType instances of the return type and arguments for a ProgModel
739 /// builtin function signature.
740 /// \param Context (in) The Context instance.
741 /// \param Builtin (in) The signature currently handled.
742 /// \param GenTypeMaxCnt (out) Maximum number of types contained in a generic
743 /// type used as return type or as argument.
744 /// Only meaningful for generic types, otherwise equals 1.
745 /// \param RetTypes (out) List of the possible return types.
746 /// \param ArgTypes (out) List of the possible argument types. For each
747 /// argument, ArgTypes contains QualTypes for the Cartesian product
748 /// of (vector sizes) x (types) .
749 template <typename ProgModel>
750 static void GetQualTypesForProgModelBuiltin(
751  Sema &S, const typename ProgModel::BuiltinStruct &Builtin,
752  unsigned &GenTypeMaxCnt, SmallVector<QualType, 1> &RetTypes,
753  SmallVector<SmallVector<QualType, 1>, 5> &ArgTypes) {
754  // Get the QualType instances of the return types.
755  unsigned Sig = ProgModel::SignatureTable[Builtin.SigTableIndex];
756  ProgModel::Bultin2Qual(S, ProgModel::TypeTable[Sig], RetTypes);
757  GenTypeMaxCnt = RetTypes.size();
758 
759  // Get the QualType instances of the arguments.
760  // First type is the return type, skip it.
761  for (unsigned Index = 1; Index < Builtin.NumTypes; Index++) {
762  SmallVector<QualType, 1> Ty;
763  ProgModel::Bultin2Qual(
764  S,
765  ProgModel::TypeTable[ProgModel::SignatureTable[Builtin.SigTableIndex +
766  Index]],
767  Ty);
768  GenTypeMaxCnt = (Ty.size() > GenTypeMaxCnt) ? Ty.size() : GenTypeMaxCnt;
769  ArgTypes.push_back(std::move(Ty));
770  }
771 }
772 
773 /// Create a list of the candidate function overloads for a ProgModel builtin
774 /// function.
775 /// \param Context (in) The ASTContext instance.
776 /// \param GenTypeMaxCnt (in) Maximum number of types contained in a generic
777 /// type used as return type or as argument.
778 /// Only meaningful for generic types, otherwise equals 1.
779 /// \param FunctionList (out) List of FunctionTypes.
780 /// \param RetTypes (in) List of the possible return types.
781 /// \param ArgTypes (in) List of the possible types for the arguments.
782 static void GetProgModelBuiltinFctOverloads(
783  ASTContext &Context, unsigned GenTypeMaxCnt,
784  std::vector<QualType> &FunctionList, SmallVector<QualType, 1> &RetTypes,
785  SmallVector<SmallVector<QualType, 1>, 5> &ArgTypes, bool IsVariadic) {
786  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo PI(
787  Context.getDefaultCallingConvention(false, false, true));
788  PI.Variadic = IsVariadic;
789 
790  // Do not attempt to create any FunctionTypes if there are no return types,
791  // which happens when a type belongs to a disabled extension.
792  if (RetTypes.size() == 0)
793  return;
794 
795  // Create FunctionTypes for each (gen)type.
796  for (unsigned IGenType = 0; IGenType < GenTypeMaxCnt; IGenType++) {
797  SmallVector<QualType, 5> ArgList;
798 
799  for (unsigned A = 0; A < ArgTypes.size(); A++) {
800  // Bail out if there is an argument that has no available types.
801  if (ArgTypes[A].size() == 0)
802  return;
803 
804  // Builtins such as "max" have an "sgentype" argument that represents
805  // the corresponding scalar type of a gentype. The number of gentypes
806  // must be a multiple of the number of sgentypes.
807  assert(GenTypeMaxCnt % ArgTypes[A].size() == 0 &&
808  "argument type count not compatible with gentype type count");
809  unsigned Idx = IGenType % ArgTypes[A].size();
810  ArgList.push_back(ArgTypes[A][Idx]);
811  }
812 
813  FunctionList.push_back(Context.getFunctionType(
814  RetTypes[(RetTypes.size() != 1) ? IGenType : 0], ArgList, PI));
815  }
816 }
817 
818 template <typename ProgModel>
819 static bool isVersionInMask(const LangOptions &O, unsigned Mask);
820 template <>
821 bool isVersionInMask<OpenCLBuiltin>(const LangOptions &LO, unsigned Mask) {
822  return isOpenCLVersionContainedInMask(LO, Mask);
823 }
824 
825 // SPIRV Builtins are always permitted, since all builtins are 'SPIRV_ALL'. We
826 // have no corresponding language option to check, so we always include them.
827 template <>
828 bool isVersionInMask<SPIRVBuiltin>(const LangOptions &LO, unsigned Mask) {
829  return true;
830 }
831 
832 /// When trying to resolve a function name, if ProgModel::isBuiltin() returns a
833 /// non-null <Index, Len> pair, then the name is referencing a
834 /// builtin function. Add all candidate signatures to the LookUpResult.
835 ///
836 /// \param S (in) The Sema instance.
837 /// \param LR (inout) The LookupResult instance.
838 /// \param II (in) The identifier being resolved.
839 /// \param FctIndex (in) Starting index in the BuiltinTable.
840 /// \param Len (in) The signature list has Len elements.
841 template <typename ProgModel>
842 static void InsertBuiltinDeclarationsFromTable(
843  Sema &S, LookupResult &LR, IdentifierInfo *II, const unsigned FctIndex,
844  const unsigned Len,
845  std::function<void(const typename ProgModel::BuiltinStruct &,
846  FunctionDecl &)>
847  ProgModelFinalizer) {
848  // The builtin function declaration uses generic types (gentype).
849  bool HasGenType = false;
850 
851  // Maximum number of types contained in a generic type used as return type or
852  // as argument. Only meaningful for generic types, otherwise equals 1.
853  unsigned GenTypeMaxCnt;
854 
855  ASTContext &Context = S.Context;
856 
857  for (unsigned SignatureIndex = 0; SignatureIndex < Len; SignatureIndex++) {
858  const typename ProgModel::BuiltinStruct &Builtin =
859  ProgModel::BuiltinTable[FctIndex + SignatureIndex];
860 
861  // Ignore this builtin function if it is not available in the currently
862  // selected language version.
863  if (!isVersionInMask<ProgModel>(Context.getLangOpts(), Builtin.Versions))
864  continue;
865 
866  // Ignore this builtin function if it carries an extension macro that is
867  // not defined. This indicates that the extension is not supported by the
868  // target, so the builtin function should not be available.
869  StringRef Extensions = ProgModel::FunctionExtensionTable[Builtin.Extension];
870  if (!Extensions.empty()) {
871  SmallVector<StringRef, 2> ExtVec;
872  Extensions.split(ExtVec, " ");
873  bool AllExtensionsDefined = true;
874  for (StringRef Ext : ExtVec) {
875  if (!S.getPreprocessor().isMacroDefined(Ext)) {
876  AllExtensionsDefined = false;
877  break;
878  }
879  }
880  if (!AllExtensionsDefined)
881  continue;
882  }
883 
884  SmallVector<QualType, 1> RetTypes;
885  SmallVector<SmallVector<QualType, 1>, 5> ArgTypes;
886 
887  // Obtain QualType lists for the function signature.
888  GetQualTypesForProgModelBuiltin<ProgModel>(S, Builtin, GenTypeMaxCnt,
889  RetTypes, ArgTypes);
890  if (GenTypeMaxCnt > 1) {
891  HasGenType = true;
892  }
893 
894  // Create function overload for each type combination.
895  std::vector<QualType> FunctionList;
896  GetProgModelBuiltinFctOverloads(Context, GenTypeMaxCnt, FunctionList,
897  RetTypes, ArgTypes, Builtin.IsVariadic);
898 
899  SourceLocation Loc = LR.getNameLoc();
900  DeclContext *Parent = Context.getTranslationUnitDecl();
901  FunctionDecl *NewBuiltin;
902 
903  for (const auto &FTy : FunctionList) {
904  NewBuiltin = FunctionDecl::Create(
905  Context, Parent, Loc, Loc, II, FTy, /*TInfo=*/nullptr, SC_Extern,
906  S.getCurFPFeatures().isFPConstrained(), false,
907  FTy->isFunctionProtoType());
908  NewBuiltin->setImplicit();
909 
910  // Create Decl objects for each parameter, adding them to the
911  // FunctionDecl.
912  const auto *FP = cast<FunctionProtoType>(FTy);
913  SmallVector<ParmVarDecl *, 4> ParmList;
914  for (unsigned IParm = 0, e = FP->getNumParams(); IParm != e; ++IParm) {
915  ParmVarDecl *Parm = ParmVarDecl::Create(
916  Context, NewBuiltin, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
917  nullptr, FP->getParamType(IParm), nullptr, SC_None, nullptr);
918  Parm->setScopeInfo(0, IParm);
919  ParmList.push_back(Parm);
920  }
921  NewBuiltin->setParams(ParmList);
922 
923  // Add function attributes.
924  if (Builtin.IsPure)
925  NewBuiltin->addAttr(PureAttr::CreateImplicit(Context));
926  if (Builtin.IsConst)
927  NewBuiltin->addAttr(ConstAttr::CreateImplicit(Context));
928  if (Builtin.IsConv)
929  NewBuiltin->addAttr(ConvergentAttr::CreateImplicit(Context));
930  if (!S.getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus)
931  NewBuiltin->addAttr(OverloadableAttr::CreateImplicit(Context));
932 
933  ProgModelFinalizer(Builtin, *NewBuiltin);
934  LR.addDecl(NewBuiltin);
935  }
936  }
937 
938  // If we added overloads, need to resolve the lookup result.
939  if (Len > 1 || HasGenType)
940  LR.resolveKind();
941 }
942 
943 /// Lookup a builtin function, when name lookup would otherwise
944 /// fail.
945 bool Sema::LookupBuiltin(LookupResult &R) {
946  Sema::LookupNameKind NameKind = R.getLookupKind();
947 
948  // If we didn't find a use of this identifier, and if the identifier
949  // corresponds to a compiler builtin, create the decl object for the builtin
950  // now, injecting it into translation unit scope, and return it.
951  if (NameKind == Sema::LookupOrdinaryName ||
952  NameKind == Sema::LookupRedeclarationWithLinkage) {
953  IdentifierInfo *II = R.getLookupName().getAsIdentifierInfo();
954  if (II) {
955  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && NameKind == Sema::LookupOrdinaryName) {
956  if (II == getASTContext().getMakeIntegerSeqName()) {
957  R.addDecl(getASTContext().getMakeIntegerSeqDecl());
958  return true;
959  } else if (II == getASTContext().getTypePackElementName()) {
960  R.addDecl(getASTContext().getTypePackElementDecl());
961  return true;
962  }
963  }
964 
965  // Check if this is an OpenCL Builtin, and if so, insert its overloads.
966  if (getLangOpts().OpenCL && getLangOpts().DeclareOpenCLBuiltins) {
967  auto Index = OpenCLBuiltin::isBuiltin(II->getName());
968  if (Index.first) {
969  InsertBuiltinDeclarationsFromTable<OpenCLBuiltin>(
970  *this, R, II, Index.first - 1, Index.second,
971  [this](const OpenCLBuiltin::BuiltinStruct &OpenCLBuiltin,
972  FunctionDecl &NewOpenCLBuiltin) {
973  if (!this->getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus)
974  NewOpenCLBuiltin.addAttr(
975  OverloadableAttr::CreateImplicit(Context));
976  });
977  return true;
978  }
979  }
980 
981  // Check if this is a SPIR-V Builtin, and if so, insert its overloads.
982  if (getLangOpts().DeclareSPIRVBuiltins) {
983  auto Index = SPIRVBuiltin::isBuiltin(II->getName());
984  if (Index.first) {
985  InsertBuiltinDeclarationsFromTable<SPIRVBuiltin>(
986  *this, R, II, Index.first - 1, Index.second,
987  [this](const SPIRVBuiltin::BuiltinStruct &,
988  FunctionDecl &NewBuiltin) {
989  if (!this->getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
990  NewBuiltin.addAttr(OverloadableAttr::CreateImplicit(Context));
991  if (this->getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice)
992  NewBuiltin.addAttr(
993  SYCLDeviceAttr::CreateImplicit(this->Context));
994  });
995  return true;
996  }
997  }
998 
999  if (DeclareRISCVVBuiltins || DeclareRISCVSiFiveVectorBuiltins) {
1000  if (!RVIntrinsicManager)
1001  RVIntrinsicManager = CreateRISCVIntrinsicManager(*this);
1002 
1003  RVIntrinsicManager->InitIntrinsicList();
1004 
1005  if (RVIntrinsicManager->CreateIntrinsicIfFound(R, II, PP))
1006  return true;
1007  }
1008 
1009  // If this is a builtin on this (or all) targets, create the decl.
1010  if (unsigned BuiltinID = II->getBuiltinID()) {
1011  // In C++ and OpenCL (spec v1.2 s6.9.f), we don't have any predefined
1012  // library functions like 'malloc'. Instead, we'll just error.
1013  if ((getLangOpts().CPlusPlus || getLangOpts().OpenCL) &&
1014  Context.BuiltinInfo.isPredefinedLibFunction(BuiltinID))
1015  return false;
1016 
1017  if (NamedDecl *D =
1018  LazilyCreateBuiltin(II, BuiltinID, TUScope,
1019  R.isForRedeclaration(), R.getNameLoc())) {
1020  R.addDecl(D);
1021  return true;
1022  }
1023  }
1024  }
1025  }
1026 
1027  return false;
1028 }
1029 
1030 /// Looks up the declaration of "struct objc_super" and
1031 /// saves it for later use in building builtin declaration of
1032 /// objc_msgSendSuper and objc_msgSendSuper_stret.
1033 static void LookupPredefedObjCSuperType(Sema &Sema, Scope *S) {
1034  ASTContext &Context = Sema.Context;
1035  LookupResult Result(Sema, &Context.Idents.get("objc_super"), SourceLocation(),
1036  Sema::LookupTagName);
1037  Sema.LookupName(Result, S);
1038  if (Result.getResultKind() == LookupResult::Found)
1039  if (const TagDecl *TD = Result.getAsSingle<TagDecl>())
1040  Context.setObjCSuperType(Context.getTagDeclType(TD));
1041 }

1043 void Sema::LookupNecessaryTypesForBuiltin(Scope *S, unsigned ID) {
1044  if (ID == Builtin::BIobjc_msgSendSuper)
1045  LookupPredefedObjCSuperType(*this, S);

1047 
1048 /// Determine whether we can declare a special member function within
1049 /// the class at this point.
1050 static bool CanDeclareSpecialMemberFunction(const CXXRecordDecl *Class) {
1051  // We need to have a definition for the class.
1052  if (!Class->getDefinition() || Class->isDependentContext())
1053  return false;
1054 
1055  // We can't be in the middle of defining the class.
1056  return !Class->isBeingDefined();
1057 }
1058 
1059 void Sema::ForceDeclarationOfImplicitMembers(CXXRecordDecl *Class) {
1060  if (!CanDeclareSpecialMemberFunction(Class))
1061  return;
1062 
1063  // If the default constructor has not yet been declared, do so now.
1064  if (Class->needsImplicitDefaultConstructor())
1065  DeclareImplicitDefaultConstructor(Class);
1066 
1067  // If the copy constructor has not yet been declared, do so now.
1068  if (Class->needsImplicitCopyConstructor())
1069  DeclareImplicitCopyConstructor(Class);
1070 
1071  // If the copy assignment operator has not yet been declared, do so now.
1072  if (Class->needsImplicitCopyAssignment())
1073  DeclareImplicitCopyAssignment(Class);
1074 
1075  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
1076  // If the move constructor has not yet been declared, do so now.
1077  if (Class->needsImplicitMoveConstructor())
1078  DeclareImplicitMoveConstructor(Class);
1079 
1080  // If the move assignment operator has not yet been declared, do so now.
1081  if (Class->needsImplicitMoveAssignment())
1082  DeclareImplicitMoveAssignment(Class);
1083  }
1084 
1085  // If the destructor has not yet been declared, do so now.
1086  if (Class->needsImplicitDestructor())
1087  DeclareImplicitDestructor(Class);
1088 }
1089 
1090 /// Determine whether this is the name of an implicitly-declared
1091 /// special member function.
1092 static bool isImplicitlyDeclaredMemberFunctionName(DeclarationName Name) {
1093  switch (Name.getNameKind()) {
1094  case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
1095  case DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName:
1096  return true;
1097 
1098  case DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName:
1099  return Name.getCXXOverloadedOperator() == OO_Equal;
1100 
1101  default:
1102  break;
1103  }
1104 
1105  return false;
1106 }
1107 
1108 /// If there are any implicit member functions with the given name
1109 /// that need to be declared in the given declaration context, do so.
1110 static void DeclareImplicitMemberFunctionsWithName(Sema &S,
1111  DeclarationName Name,
1112  SourceLocation Loc,
1113  const DeclContext *DC) {
1114  if (!DC)
1115  return;
1116 
1117  switch (Name.getNameKind()) {
1118  case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
1119  if (const CXXRecordDecl *Record = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DC))
1120  if (Record->getDefinition() && CanDeclareSpecialMemberFunction(Record)) {
1121  CXXRecordDecl *Class = const_cast<CXXRecordDecl *>(Record);
1122  if (Record->needsImplicitDefaultConstructor())
1123  S.DeclareImplicitDefaultConstructor(Class);
1124  if (Record->needsImplicitCopyConstructor())
1125  S.DeclareImplicitCopyConstructor(Class);
1126  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 &&
1127  Record->needsImplicitMoveConstructor())
1128  S.DeclareImplicitMoveConstructor(Class);
1129  }
1130  break;
1131 
1132  case DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName:
1133  if (const CXXRecordDecl *Record = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DC))
1134  if (Record->getDefinition() && Record->needsImplicitDestructor() &&
1135  CanDeclareSpecialMemberFunction(Record))
1136  S.DeclareImplicitDestructor(const_cast<CXXRecordDecl *>(Record));
1137  break;
1138 
1139  case DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName:
1140  if (Name.getCXXOverloadedOperator() != OO_Equal)
1141  break;
1142 
1143  if (const CXXRecordDecl *Record = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DC)) {
1144  if (Record->getDefinition() && CanDeclareSpecialMemberFunction(Record)) {
1145  CXXRecordDecl *Class = const_cast<CXXRecordDecl *>(Record);
1146  if (Record->needsImplicitCopyAssignment())
1147  S.DeclareImplicitCopyAssignment(Class);
1148  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 &&
1149  Record->needsImplicitMoveAssignment())
1150  S.DeclareImplicitMoveAssignment(Class);
1151  }
1152  }
1153  break;
1154 
1155  case DeclarationName::CXXDeductionGuideName:
1156  S.DeclareImplicitDeductionGuides(Name.getCXXDeductionGuideTemplate(), Loc);
1157  break;
1158 
1159  default:
1160  break;
1161  }
1162 }
1163 
1164 // Adds all qualifying matches for a name within a decl context to the
1165 // given lookup result. Returns true if any matches were found.
1166 static bool LookupDirect(Sema &S, LookupResult &R, const DeclContext *DC) {
1167  bool Found = false;
1168 
1169  // Lazily declare C++ special member functions.
1170  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
1171  DeclareImplicitMemberFunctionsWithName(S, R.getLookupName(), R.getNameLoc(),
1172  DC);
1173 
1174  // Perform lookup into this declaration context.
1175  DeclContext::lookup_result DR = DC->lookup(R.getLookupName());
1176  for (NamedDecl *D : DR) {
1177  if ((D = R.getAcceptableDecl(D))) {
1178  R.addDecl(D);
1179  Found = true;
1180  }
1181  }
1182 
1183  if (!Found && DC->isTranslationUnit() && S.LookupBuiltin(R))
1184  return true;
1185 
1186  if (R.getLookupName().getNameKind()
1187  != DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName ||
1188  R.getLookupName().getCXXNameType()->isDependentType() ||
1189  !isa<CXXRecordDecl>(DC))
1190  return Found;
1191 
1192  // C++ [temp.mem]p6:
1193  // A specialization of a conversion function template is not found by
1194  // name lookup. Instead, any conversion function templates visible in the
1195  // context of the use are considered. [...]
1196  const CXXRecordDecl *Record = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DC);
1197  if (!Record->isCompleteDefinition())
1198  return Found;
1199 
1200  // For conversion operators, 'operator auto' should only match
1201  // 'operator auto'. Since 'auto' is not a type, it shouldn't be considered
1202  // as a candidate for template substitution.
1203  auto *ContainedDeducedType =
1204  R.getLookupName().getCXXNameType()->getContainedDeducedType();
1205  if (R.getLookupName().getNameKind() ==
1206  DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName &&
1207  ContainedDeducedType && ContainedDeducedType->isUndeducedType())
1208  return Found;
1209 
1210  for (CXXRecordDecl::conversion_iterator U = Record->conversion_begin(),
1211  UEnd = Record->conversion_end(); U != UEnd; ++U) {
1212  FunctionTemplateDecl *ConvTemplate = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(*U);
1213  if (!ConvTemplate)
1214  continue;
1215 
1216  // When we're performing lookup for the purposes of redeclaration, just
1217  // add the conversion function template. When we deduce template
1218  // arguments for specializations, we'll end up unifying the return
1219  // type of the new declaration with the type of the function template.
1220  if (R.isForRedeclaration()) {
1221  R.addDecl(ConvTemplate);
1222  Found = true;
1223  continue;
1224  }
1225 
1226  // C++ [temp.mem]p6:
1227  // [...] For each such operator, if argument deduction succeeds
1228  // (14.9.2.3), the resulting specialization is used as if found by
1229  // name lookup.
1230  //
1231  // When referencing a conversion function for any purpose other than
1232  // a redeclaration (such that we'll be building an expression with the
1233  // result), perform template argument deduction and place the
1234  // specialization into the result set. We do this to avoid forcing all
1235  // callers to perform special deduction for conversion functions.
1236  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(R.getNameLoc());
1237  FunctionDecl *Specialization = nullptr;
1238 
1239  const FunctionProtoType *ConvProto
1240  = ConvTemplate->getTemplatedDecl()->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
1241  assert(ConvProto && "Nonsensical conversion function template type");
1242 
1243  // Compute the type of the function that we would expect the conversion
1244  // function to have, if it were to match the name given.
1245  // FIXME: Calling convention!
1246  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = ConvProto->getExtProtoInfo();
1247  EPI.ExtInfo = EPI.ExtInfo.withCallingConv(CC_C);
1248  EPI.ExceptionSpec = EST_None;
1249  QualType ExpectedType = R.getSema().Context.getFunctionType(
1250  R.getLookupName().getCXXNameType(), std::nullopt, EPI);
1251 
1252  // Perform template argument deduction against the type that we would
1253  // expect the function to have.
1254  if (R.getSema().DeduceTemplateArguments(ConvTemplate, nullptr, ExpectedType,
1255  Specialization, Info) ==
1256  TemplateDeductionResult::Success) {
1257  R.addDecl(Specialization);
1258  Found = true;
1259  }
1260  }
1261 
1262  return Found;
1263 }
1264 
1265 // Performs C++ unqualified lookup into the given file context.
1266 static bool CppNamespaceLookup(Sema &S, LookupResult &R, ASTContext &Context,
1267  const DeclContext *NS,
1268  UnqualUsingDirectiveSet &UDirs) {
1269 
1270  assert(NS && NS->isFileContext() && "CppNamespaceLookup() requires namespace!");
1271 
1272  // Perform direct name lookup into the LookupCtx.
1273  bool Found = LookupDirect(S, R, NS);
1274 
1275  // Perform direct name lookup into the namespaces nominated by the
1276  // using directives whose common ancestor is this namespace.
1277  for (const UnqualUsingEntry &UUE : UDirs.getNamespacesFor(NS))
1278  if (LookupDirect(S, R, UUE.getNominatedNamespace()))
1279  Found = true;
1280 
1281  R.resolveKind();
1282 
1283  return Found;
1284 }
1285 
1286 static bool isNamespaceOrTranslationUnitScope(Scope *S) {
1287  if (DeclContext *Ctx = S->getEntity())
1288  return Ctx->isFileContext();
1289  return false;
1290 }
1291 
1292 /// Find the outer declaration context from this scope. This indicates the
1293 /// context that we should search up to (exclusive) before considering the
1294 /// parent of the specified scope.
1295 static DeclContext *findOuterContext(Scope *S) {
1296  for (Scope *OuterS = S->getParent(); OuterS; OuterS = OuterS->getParent())
1297  if (DeclContext *DC = OuterS->getLookupEntity())
1298  return DC;
1299  return nullptr;
1300 }
1301 
1302 namespace {
1303 /// An RAII object to specify that we want to find block scope extern
1304 /// declarations.
1305 struct FindLocalExternScope {
1306  FindLocalExternScope(LookupResult &R)
1307  : R(R), OldFindLocalExtern(R.getIdentifierNamespace() &
1308  Decl::IDNS_LocalExtern) {
1309  R.setFindLocalExtern(R.getIdentifierNamespace() &
1310  (Decl::IDNS_Ordinary | Decl::IDNS_NonMemberOperator));
1311  }
1312  void restore() {
1313  R.setFindLocalExtern(OldFindLocalExtern);
1314  }
1315  ~FindLocalExternScope() {
1316  restore();
1317  }
1318  LookupResult &R;
1319  bool OldFindLocalExtern;
1320 };
1321 } // end anonymous namespace
1322 
1323 bool Sema::CppLookupName(LookupResult &R, Scope *S) {
1324  assert(getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && "Can perform only C++ lookup");
1325 
1326  DeclarationName Name = R.getLookupName();
1327  Sema::LookupNameKind NameKind = R.getLookupKind();
1328 
1329  // If this is the name of an implicitly-declared special member function,
1330  // go through the scope stack to implicitly declare
1331  if (isImplicitlyDeclaredMemberFunctionName(Name)) {
1332  for (Scope *PreS = S; PreS; PreS = PreS->getParent())
1333  if (DeclContext *DC = PreS->getEntity())
1334  DeclareImplicitMemberFunctionsWithName(*this, Name, R.getNameLoc(), DC);
1335  }
1336 
1337  // Implicitly declare member functions with the name we're looking for, if in
1338  // fact we are in a scope where it matters.
1339 
1340  Scope *Initial = S;
1341  IdentifierResolver::iterator
1342  I = IdResolver.begin(Name),
1343  IEnd = IdResolver.end();
1344 
1345  // First we lookup local scope.
1346  // We don't consider using-directives, as per 7.3.4.p1 [namespace.udir]
1347  // ...During unqualified name lookup (3.4.1), the names appear as if
1348  // they were declared in the nearest enclosing namespace which contains
1349  // both the using-directive and the nominated namespace.
1350  // [Note: in this context, "contains" means "contains directly or
1351  // indirectly".
1352  //
1353  // For example:
1354  // namespace A { int i; }
1355  // void foo() {
1356  // int i;
1357  // {
1358  // using namespace A;
1359  // ++i; // finds local 'i', A::i appears at global scope
1360  // }
1361  // }
1362  //
1363  UnqualUsingDirectiveSet UDirs(*this);
1364  bool VisitedUsingDirectives = false;
1365  bool LeftStartingScope = false;
1366 
1367  // When performing a scope lookup, we want to find local extern decls.
1368  FindLocalExternScope FindLocals(R);
1369 
1370  for (; S && !isNamespaceOrTranslationUnitScope(S); S = S->getParent()) {
1371  bool SearchNamespaceScope = true;
1372  // Check whether the IdResolver has anything in this scope.
1373  for (; I != IEnd && S->isDeclScope(*I); ++I) {
1374  if (NamedDecl *ND = R.getAcceptableDecl(*I)) {
1375  if (NameKind == LookupRedeclarationWithLinkage &&
1376  !(*I)->isTemplateParameter()) {
1377  // If it's a template parameter, we still find it, so we can diagnose
1378  // the invalid redeclaration.
1379 
1380  // Determine whether this (or a previous) declaration is
1381  // out-of-scope.
1382  if (!LeftStartingScope && !Initial->isDeclScope(*I))
1383  LeftStartingScope = true;
1384 
1385  // If we found something outside of our starting scope that
1386  // does not have linkage, skip it.
1387  if (LeftStartingScope && !((*I)->hasLinkage())) {
1388  R.setShadowed();
1389  continue;
1390  }
1391  } else {
1392  // We found something in this scope, we should not look at the
1393  // namespace scope
1394  SearchNamespaceScope = false;
1395  }
1396  R.addDecl(ND);
1397  }
1398  }
1399  if (!SearchNamespaceScope) {
1400  R.resolveKind();
1401  if (S->isClassScope())
1402  if (auto *Record = dyn_cast_if_present<CXXRecordDecl>(S->getEntity()))
1403  R.setNamingClass(Record);
1404  return true;
1405  }
1406 
1407  if (NameKind == LookupLocalFriendName && !S->isClassScope()) {
1408  // C++11 [class.friend]p11:
1409  // If a friend declaration appears in a local class and the name
1410  // specified is an unqualified name, a prior declaration is
1411  // looked up without considering scopes that are outside the
1412  // innermost enclosing non-class scope.
1413  return false;
1414  }
1415 
1416  if (DeclContext *Ctx = S->getLookupEntity()) {
1417  DeclContext *OuterCtx = findOuterContext(S);
1418  for (; Ctx && !Ctx->Equals(OuterCtx); Ctx = Ctx->getLookupParent()) {
1419  // We do not directly look into transparent contexts, since
1420  // those entities will be found in the nearest enclosing
1421  // non-transparent context.
1422  if (Ctx->isTransparentContext())
1423  continue;
1424 
1425  // We do not look directly into function or method contexts,
1426  // since all of the local variables and parameters of the
1427  // function/method are present within the Scope.
1428  if (Ctx->isFunctionOrMethod()) {
1429  // If we have an Objective-C instance method, look for ivars
1430  // in the corresponding interface.
1431  if (ObjCMethodDecl *Method = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(Ctx)) {
1432  if (Method->isInstanceMethod() && Name.getAsIdentifierInfo())
1433  if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class = Method->getClassInterface()) {
1434  ObjCInterfaceDecl *ClassDeclared;
1435  if (ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar = Class->lookupInstanceVariable(
1436  Name.getAsIdentifierInfo(),
1437  ClassDeclared)) {
1438  if (NamedDecl *ND = R.getAcceptableDecl(Ivar)) {
1439  R.addDecl(ND);
1440  R.resolveKind();
1441  return true;
1442  }
1443  }
1444  }
1445  }
1446 
1447  continue;
1448  }
1449 
1450  // If this is a file context, we need to perform unqualified name
1451  // lookup considering using directives.
1452  if (Ctx->isFileContext()) {
1453  // If we haven't handled using directives yet, do so now.
1454  if (!VisitedUsingDirectives) {
1455  // Add using directives from this context up to the top level.
1456  for (DeclContext *UCtx = Ctx; UCtx; UCtx = UCtx->getParent()) {
1457  if (UCtx->isTransparentContext())
1458  continue;
1459 
1460  UDirs.visit(UCtx, UCtx);
1461  }
1462 
1463  // Find the innermost file scope, so we can add using directives
1464  // from local scopes.
1465  Scope *InnermostFileScope = S;
1466  while (InnermostFileScope &&
1467  !isNamespaceOrTranslationUnitScope(InnermostFileScope))
1468  InnermostFileScope = InnermostFileScope->getParent();
1469  UDirs.visitScopeChain(Initial, InnermostFileScope);
1470 
1471  UDirs.done();
1472 
1473  VisitedUsingDirectives = true;
1474  }
1475 
1476  if (CppNamespaceLookup(*this, R, Context, Ctx, UDirs)) {
1477  R.resolveKind();
1478  return true;
1479  }
1480 
1481  continue;
1482  }
1483 
1484  // Perform qualified name lookup into this context.
1485  // FIXME: In some cases, we know that every name that could be found by
1486  // this qualified name lookup will also be on the identifier chain. For
1487  // example, inside a class without any base classes, we never need to
1488  // perform qualified lookup because all of the members are on top of the
1489  // identifier chain.
1490  if (LookupQualifiedName(R, Ctx, /*InUnqualifiedLookup=*/true))
1491  return true;
1492  }
1493  }
1494  }
1495 
1496  // Stop if we ran out of scopes.
1497  // FIXME: This really, really shouldn't be happening.
1498  if (!S) return false;
1499 
1500  // If we are looking for members, no need to look into global/namespace scope.
1501  if (NameKind == LookupMemberName)
1502  return false;
1503 
1504  // Collect UsingDirectiveDecls in all scopes, and recursively all
1505  // nominated namespaces by those using-directives.
1506  //
1507  // FIXME: Cache this sorted list in Scope structure, and DeclContext, so we
1508  // don't build it for each lookup!
1509  if (!VisitedUsingDirectives) {
1510  UDirs.visitScopeChain(Initial, S);
1511  UDirs.done();
1512  }
1513 
1514  // If we're not performing redeclaration lookup, do not look for local
1515  // extern declarations outside of a function scope.
1516  if (!R.isForRedeclaration())
1517  FindLocals.restore();
1518 
1519  // Lookup namespace scope, and global scope.
1520  // Unqualified name lookup in C++ requires looking into scopes
1521  // that aren't strictly lexical, and therefore we walk through the
1522  // context as well as walking through the scopes.
1523  for (; S; S = S->getParent()) {
1524  // Check whether the IdResolver has anything in this scope.
1525  bool Found = false;
1526  for (; I != IEnd && S->isDeclScope(*I); ++I) {
1527  if (NamedDecl *ND = R.getAcceptableDecl(*I)) {
1528  // We found something. Look for anything else in our scope
1529  // with this same name and in an acceptable identifier
1530  // namespace, so that we can construct an overload set if we
1531  // need to.
1532  Found = true;
1533  R.addDecl(ND);
1534  }
1535  }
1536 
1537  if (Found && S->isTemplateParamScope()) {
1538  R.resolveKind();
1539  return true;
1540  }
1541 
1542  DeclContext *Ctx = S->getLookupEntity();
1543  if (Ctx) {
1544  DeclContext *OuterCtx = findOuterContext(S);
1545  for (; Ctx && !Ctx->Equals(OuterCtx); Ctx = Ctx->getLookupParent()) {
1546  // We do not directly look into transparent contexts, since
1547  // those entities will be found in the nearest enclosing
1548  // non-transparent context.
1549  if (Ctx->isTransparentContext())
1550  continue;
1551 
1552  // If we have a context, and it's not a context stashed in the
1553  // template parameter scope for an out-of-line definition, also
1554  // look into that context.
1555  if (!(Found && S->isTemplateParamScope())) {
1556  assert(Ctx->isFileContext() &&
1557  "We should have been looking only at file context here already.");
1558 
1559  // Look into context considering using-directives.
1560  if (CppNamespaceLookup(*this, R, Context, Ctx, UDirs))
1561  Found = true;
1562  }
1563 
1564  if (Found) {
1565  R.resolveKind();
1566  return true;
1567  }
1568 
1569  if (R.isForRedeclaration() && !Ctx->isTransparentContext())
1570  return false;
1571  }
1572  }
1573 
1574  if (R.isForRedeclaration() && Ctx && !Ctx->isTransparentContext())
1575  return false;
1576  }
1577 
1578  return !R.empty();
1579 }
1580 
1581 void Sema::makeMergedDefinitionVisible(NamedDecl *ND) {
1582  if (auto *M = getCurrentModule())
1583  Context.mergeDefinitionIntoModule(ND, M);
1584  else
1585  // We're not building a module; just make the definition visible.
1586  ND->setVisibleDespiteOwningModule();
1587 
1588  // If ND is a template declaration, make the template parameters
1589  // visible too. They're not (necessarily) within a mergeable DeclContext.
1590  if (auto *TD = dyn_cast<TemplateDecl>(ND))
1591  for (auto *Param : *TD->getTemplateParameters())
1592  makeMergedDefinitionVisible(Param);
1593 }
1594 
1595 /// Find the module in which the given declaration was defined.
1596 static Module *getDefiningModule(Sema &S, Decl *Entity) {
1597  if (FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Entity)) {
1598  // If this function was instantiated from a template, the defining module is
1599  // the module containing the pattern.
1600  if (FunctionDecl *Pattern = FD->getTemplateInstantiationPattern())
1601  Entity = Pattern;
1602  } else if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Entity)) {
1603  if (CXXRecordDecl *Pattern = RD->getTemplateInstantiationPattern())
1604  Entity = Pattern;
1605  } else if (EnumDecl *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(Entity)) {
1606  if (auto *Pattern = ED->getTemplateInstantiationPattern())
1607  Entity = Pattern;
1608  } else if (VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Entity)) {
1609  if (VarDecl *Pattern = VD->getTemplateInstantiationPattern())
1610  Entity = Pattern;
1611  }
1612 
1613  // Walk up to the containing context. That might also have been instantiated
1614  // from a template.
1615  DeclContext *Context = Entity->getLexicalDeclContext();
1616  if (Context->isFileContext())
1617  return S.getOwningModule(Entity);
1618  return getDefiningModule(S, cast<Decl>(Context));
1619 }
1620 
1621 llvm::DenseSet<Module*> &Sema::getLookupModules() {
1622  unsigned N = CodeSynthesisContexts.size();
1623  for (unsigned I = CodeSynthesisContextLookupModules.size();
1624  I != N; ++I) {
1625  Module *M = CodeSynthesisContexts[I].Entity ?
1626  getDefiningModule(*this, CodeSynthesisContexts[I].Entity) :
1627  nullptr;
1628  if (M && !LookupModulesCache.insert(M).second)
1629  M = nullptr;
1630  CodeSynthesisContextLookupModules.push_back(M);
1631  }
1632  return LookupModulesCache;
1633 }
1634 
1635 /// Determine if we could use all the declarations in the module.
1636 bool Sema::isUsableModule(const Module *M) {
1637  assert(M && "We shouldn't check nullness for module here");
1638  // Return quickly if we cached the result.
1639  if (UsableModuleUnitsCache.count(M))
1640  return true;
1641 
1642  // If M is the global module fragment of the current translation unit. So it
1643  // should be usable.
1644  // [module.global.frag]p1:
1645  // The global module fragment can be used to provide declarations that are
1646  // attached to the global module and usable within the module unit.
1647  if (M == TheGlobalModuleFragment || M == TheImplicitGlobalModuleFragment ||
1648  // If M is the module we're parsing, it should be usable. This covers the
1649  // private module fragment. The private module fragment is usable only if
1650  // it is within the current module unit. And it must be the current
1651  // parsing module unit if it is within the current module unit according
1652  // to the grammar of the private module fragment. NOTE: This is covered by
1653  // the following condition. The intention of the check is to avoid string
1654  // comparison as much as possible.
1655  M == getCurrentModule() ||
1656  // The module unit which is in the same module with the current module
1657  // unit is usable.
1658  //
1659  // FIXME: Here we judge if they are in the same module by comparing the
1660  // string. Is there any better solution?
1661  M->getPrimaryModuleInterfaceName() ==
1662  llvm::StringRef(getLangOpts().CurrentModule).split(':').first) {
1663  UsableModuleUnitsCache.insert(M);
1664  return true;
1665  }
1666 
1667  return false;
1668 }
1669 
1670 bool Sema::hasVisibleMergedDefinition(const NamedDecl *Def) {
1671  for (const Module *Merged : Context.getModulesWithMergedDefinition(Def))
1672  if (isModuleVisible(Merged))
1673  return true;
1674  return false;
1675 }
1676 
1677 bool Sema::hasMergedDefinitionInCurrentModule(const NamedDecl *Def) {
1678  for (const Module *Merged : Context.getModulesWithMergedDefinition(Def))
1679  if (isUsableModule(Merged))
1680  return true;
1681  return false;
1682 }
1683 
1684 template <typename ParmDecl>
1685 static bool
1686 hasAcceptableDefaultArgument(Sema &S, const ParmDecl *D,
1687  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Module *> *Modules,
1688  Sema::AcceptableKind Kind) {
1689  if (!D->hasDefaultArgument())
1690  return false;
1691 
1692  llvm::SmallPtrSet<const ParmDecl *, 4> Visited;
1693  while (D && Visited.insert(D).second) {
1694  auto &DefaultArg = D->getDefaultArgStorage();
1695  if (!DefaultArg.isInherited() && S.isAcceptable(D, Kind))
1696  return true;
1697 
1698  if (!DefaultArg.isInherited() && Modules) {
1699  auto *NonConstD = const_cast<ParmDecl*>(D);
1700  Modules->push_back(S.getOwningModule(NonConstD));
1701  }
1702 
1703  // If there was a previous default argument, maybe its parameter is
1704  // acceptable.
1705  D = DefaultArg.getInheritedFrom();
1706  }
1707  return false;
1708 }
1709 
1710 bool Sema::hasAcceptableDefaultArgument(
1711  const NamedDecl *D, llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Module *> *Modules,
1712  Sema::AcceptableKind Kind) {
1713  if (auto *P = dyn_cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(D))
1714  return ::hasAcceptableDefaultArgument(*this, P, Modules, Kind);
1715 
1716  if (auto *P = dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(D))
1717  return ::hasAcceptableDefaultArgument(*this, P, Modules, Kind);
1718 
1719  return ::hasAcceptableDefaultArgument(
1720  *this, cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(D), Modules, Kind);
1721 }
1722 
1723 bool Sema::hasVisibleDefaultArgument(const NamedDecl *D,
1724  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Module *> *Modules) {
1725  return hasAcceptableDefaultArgument(D, Modules,
1726  Sema::AcceptableKind::Visible);
1727 }

1729 bool Sema::hasReachableDefaultArgument(
1730  const NamedDecl *D, llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Module *> *Modules) {
1731  return hasAcceptableDefaultArgument(D, Modules,
1732  Sema::AcceptableKind::Reachable);
1733 }
1734 
1735 template <typename Filter>
1736 static bool
1737 hasAcceptableDeclarationImpl(Sema &S, const NamedDecl *D,
1738  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Module *> *Modules, Filter F,
1739  Sema::AcceptableKind Kind) {
1740  bool HasFilteredRedecls = false;
1741 
1742  for (auto *Redecl : D->redecls()) {
1743  auto *R = cast<NamedDecl>(Redecl);
1744  if (!F(R))
1745  continue;
1746 
1747  if (S.isAcceptable(R, Kind))
1748  return true;
1749 
1750  HasFilteredRedecls = true;
1751 
1752  if (Modules)
1753  Modules->push_back(R->getOwningModule());
1754  }
1755 
1756  // Only return false if there is at least one redecl that is not filtered out.
1757  if (HasFilteredRedecls)
1758  return false;
1759 
1760  return true;
1761 }
1762 
1763 static bool
1764 hasAcceptableExplicitSpecialization(Sema &S, const NamedDecl *D,
1765  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Module *> *Modules,
1766  Sema::AcceptableKind Kind) {
1767  return hasAcceptableDeclarationImpl(
1768  S, D, Modules,
1769  [](const NamedDecl *D) {
1770  if (auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D))
1771  return RD->getTemplateSpecializationKind() ==
1772  TSK_ExplicitSpecialization;
1773  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
1774  return FD->getTemplateSpecializationKind() ==
1775  TSK_ExplicitSpecialization;
1776  if (auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
1777  return VD->getTemplateSpecializationKind() ==
1778  TSK_ExplicitSpecialization;
1779  llvm_unreachable("unknown explicit specialization kind");
1780  },
1781  Kind);
1782 }
1783 
1784 bool Sema::hasVisibleExplicitSpecialization(
1785  const NamedDecl *D, llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Module *> *Modules) {
1786  return ::hasAcceptableExplicitSpecialization(*this, D, Modules,
1787  Sema::AcceptableKind::Visible);
1788 }

1790 bool Sema::hasReachableExplicitSpecialization(
1791  const NamedDecl *D, llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Module *> *Modules) {
1792  return ::hasAcceptableExplicitSpecialization(*this, D, Modules,
1793  Sema::AcceptableKind::Reachable);

1796 static bool
1797 hasAcceptableMemberSpecialization(Sema &S, const NamedDecl *D,
1798  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Module *> *Modules,
1799  Sema::AcceptableKind Kind) {
1800  assert(isa<CXXRecordDecl>(D->getDeclContext()) &&
1801  "not a member specialization");
1802  return hasAcceptableDeclarationImpl(
1803  S, D, Modules,
1804  [](const NamedDecl *D) {
1805  // If the specialization is declared at namespace scope, then it's a
1806  // member specialization declaration. If it's lexically inside the class
1807  // definition then it was instantiated.
1808  //
1809  // FIXME: This is a hack. There should be a better way to determine
1810  // this.
1811  // FIXME: What about MS-style explicit specializations declared within a
1812  // class definition?
1813  return D->getLexicalDeclContext()->isFileContext();
1814  },
1815  Kind);
1816 }
1817 
1818 bool Sema::hasVisibleMemberSpecialization(
1819  const NamedDecl *D, llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Module *> *Modules) {
1820  return hasAcceptableMemberSpecialization(*this, D, Modules,
1821  Sema::AcceptableKind::Visible);
1822 }

1824 bool Sema::hasReachableMemberSpecialization(
1825  const NamedDecl *D, llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Module *> *Modules) {
1826  return hasAcceptableMemberSpecialization(*this, D, Modules,
1827  Sema::AcceptableKind::Reachable);

1829 
1830 /// Determine whether a declaration is acceptable to name lookup.
1831 ///
1832 /// This routine determines whether the declaration D is acceptable in the
1833 /// current lookup context, taking into account the current template
1834 /// instantiation stack. During template instantiation, a declaration is
1835 /// acceptable if it is acceptable from a module containing any entity on the
1836 /// template instantiation path (by instantiating a template, you allow it to
1837 /// see the declarations that your module can see, including those later on in
1838 /// your module).
1839 bool LookupResult::isAcceptableSlow(Sema &SemaRef, NamedDecl *D,
1840  Sema::AcceptableKind Kind) {
1841  assert(!D->isUnconditionallyVisible() &&
1842  "should not call this: not in slow case");
1843 
1844  Module *DeclModule = SemaRef.getOwningModule(D);
1845  assert(DeclModule && "hidden decl has no owning module");
1846 
1847  // If the owning module is visible, the decl is acceptable.
1848  if (SemaRef.isModuleVisible(DeclModule,
1849  D->isInvisibleOutsideTheOwningModule()))
1850  return true;
1851 
1852  // Determine whether a decl context is a file context for the purpose of
1853  // visibility/reachability. This looks through some (export and linkage spec)
1854  // transparent contexts, but not others (enums).
1855  auto IsEffectivelyFileContext = [](const DeclContext *DC) {
1856  return DC->isFileContext() || isa<LinkageSpecDecl>(DC) ||
1857  isa<ExportDecl>(DC);
1858  };
1859 
1860  // If this declaration is not at namespace scope
1861  // then it is acceptable if its lexical parent has a acceptable definition.
1862  DeclContext *DC = D->getLexicalDeclContext();
1863  if (DC && !IsEffectivelyFileContext(DC)) {
1864  // For a parameter, check whether our current template declaration's
1865  // lexical context is acceptable, not whether there's some other acceptable
1866  // definition of it, because parameters aren't "within" the definition.
1867  //
1868  // In C++ we need to check for a acceptable definition due to ODR merging,
1869  // and in C we must not because each declaration of a function gets its own
1870  // set of declarations for tags in prototype scope.
1871  bool AcceptableWithinParent;
1872  if (D->isTemplateParameter()) {
1873  bool SearchDefinitions = true;
1874  if (const auto *DCD = dyn_cast<Decl>(DC)) {
1875  if (const auto *TD = DCD->getDescribedTemplate()) {
1876  TemplateParameterList *TPL = TD->getTemplateParameters();
1877  auto Index = getDepthAndIndex(D).second;
1878  SearchDefinitions = Index >= TPL->size() || TPL->getParam(Index) != D;
1879  }
1880  }
1881  if (SearchDefinitions)
1882  AcceptableWithinParent =
1883  SemaRef.hasAcceptableDefinition(cast<NamedDecl>(DC), Kind);
1884  else
1885  AcceptableWithinParent =
1886  isAcceptable(SemaRef, cast<NamedDecl>(DC), Kind);
1887  } else if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(D) ||
1888  (isa<FunctionDecl>(DC) && !SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus))
1889  AcceptableWithinParent = isAcceptable(SemaRef, cast<NamedDecl>(DC), Kind);
1890  else if (D->isModulePrivate()) {
1891  // A module-private declaration is only acceptable if an enclosing lexical
1892  // parent was merged with another definition in the current module.
1893  AcceptableWithinParent = false;
1894  do {
1895  if (SemaRef.hasMergedDefinitionInCurrentModule(cast<NamedDecl>(DC))) {
1896  AcceptableWithinParent = true;
1897  break;
1898  }
1899  DC = DC->getLexicalParent();
1900  } while (!IsEffectivelyFileContext(DC));
1901  } else {
1902  AcceptableWithinParent =
1903  SemaRef.hasAcceptableDefinition(cast<NamedDecl>(DC), Kind);
1904  }
1905 
1906  if (AcceptableWithinParent && SemaRef.CodeSynthesisContexts.empty() &&
1907  Kind == Sema::AcceptableKind::Visible &&
1908  // FIXME: Do something better in this case.
1909  !SemaRef.getLangOpts().ModulesLocalVisibility) {
1910  // Cache the fact that this declaration is implicitly visible because
1911  // its parent has a visible definition.
1912  D->setVisibleDespiteOwningModule();
1913  }
1914  return AcceptableWithinParent;
1915  }
1916 
1917  if (Kind == Sema::AcceptableKind::Visible)
1918  return false;
1919 
1920  assert(Kind == Sema::AcceptableKind::Reachable &&
1921  "Additional Sema::AcceptableKind?");
1922  return isReachableSlow(SemaRef, D);
1923 }
1924 
1925 bool Sema::isModuleVisible(const Module *M, bool ModulePrivate) {
1926  // The module might be ordinarily visible. For a module-private query, that
1927  // means it is part of the current module.
1928  if (ModulePrivate && isUsableModule(M))
1929  return true;
1930 
1931  // For a query which is not module-private, that means it is in our visible
1932  // module set.
1933  if (!ModulePrivate && VisibleModules.isVisible(M))
1934  return true;
1935 
1936  // Otherwise, it might be visible by virtue of the query being within a
1937  // template instantiation or similar that is permitted to look inside M.
1938 
1939  // Find the extra places where we need to look.
1940  const auto &LookupModules = getLookupModules();
1941  if (LookupModules.empty())
1942  return false;
1943 
1944  // If our lookup set contains the module, it's visible.
1945  if (LookupModules.count(M))
1946  return true;
1947 
1948  // The global module fragments are visible to its corresponding module unit.
1949  // So the global module fragment should be visible if the its corresponding
1950  // module unit is visible.
1951  if (M->isGlobalModule() && LookupModules.count(M->getTopLevelModule()))
1952  return true;
1953 
1954  // For a module-private query, that's everywhere we get to look.
1955  if (ModulePrivate)
1956  return false;
1957 
1958  // Check whether M is transitively exported to an import of the lookup set.
1959  return llvm::any_of(LookupModules, [&](const Module *LookupM) {
1960  return LookupM->isModuleVisible(M);
1961  });
1962 }
1963 
1964 // FIXME: Return false directly if we don't have an interface dependency on the
1965 // translation unit containing D.
1966 bool LookupResult::isReachableSlow(Sema &SemaRef, NamedDecl *D) {
1967  assert(!isVisible(SemaRef, D) && "Shouldn't call the slow case.\n");
1968 
1969  Module *DeclModule = SemaRef.getOwningModule(D);
1970  assert(DeclModule && "hidden decl has no owning module");
1971 
1972  // Entities in header like modules are reachable only if they're visible.
1973  if (DeclModule->isHeaderLikeModule())
1974  return false;
1975 
1976  if (!D->isInAnotherModuleUnit())
1977  return true;
1978 
1979  // [module.reach]/p3:
1980  // A declaration D is reachable from a point P if:
1981  // ...
1982  // - D is not discarded ([module.global.frag]), appears in a translation unit
1983  // that is reachable from P, and does not appear within a private module
1984  // fragment.
1985  //
1986  // A declaration that's discarded in the GMF should be module-private.
1987  if (D->isModulePrivate())
1988  return false;
1989 
1990  // [module.reach]/p1
1991  // A translation unit U is necessarily reachable from a point P if U is a
1992  // module interface unit on which the translation unit containing P has an
1993  // interface dependency, or the translation unit containing P imports U, in
1994  // either case prior to P ([module.import]).
1995  //
1996  // [module.import]/p10
1997  // A translation unit has an interface dependency on a translation unit U if
1998  // it contains a declaration (possibly a module-declaration) that imports U
1999  // or if it has an interface dependency on a translation unit that has an
2000  // interface dependency on U.
2001  //
2002  // So we could conclude the module unit U is necessarily reachable if:
2003  // (1) The module unit U is module interface unit.
2004  // (2) The current unit has an interface dependency on the module unit U.
2005  //
2006  // Here we only check for the first condition. Since we couldn't see
2007  // DeclModule if it isn't (transitively) imported.
2008  if (DeclModule->getTopLevelModule()->isModuleInterfaceUnit())
2009  return true;
2010 
2011  // [module.reach]/p2
2012  // Additional translation units on
2013  // which the point within the program has an interface dependency may be
2014  // considered reachable, but it is unspecified which are and under what
2015  // circumstances.
2016  //
2017  // The decision here is to treat all additional tranditional units as
2018  // unreachable.
2019  return false;
2020 }
2021 
2022 bool Sema::isAcceptableSlow(const NamedDecl *D, Sema::AcceptableKind Kind) {
2023  return LookupResult::isAcceptable(*this, const_cast<NamedDecl *>(D), Kind);
2024 }
2025 
2026 bool Sema::shouldLinkPossiblyHiddenDecl(LookupResult &R, const NamedDecl *New) {
2027  // FIXME: If there are both visible and hidden declarations, we need to take
2028  // into account whether redeclaration is possible. Example:
2029  //
2030  // Non-imported module:
2031  // int f(T); // #1
2032  // Some TU:
2033  // static int f(U); // #2, not a redeclaration of #1
2034  // int f(T); // #3, finds both, should link with #1 if T != U, but
2035  // // with #2 if T == U; neither should be ambiguous.
2036  for (auto *D : R) {
2037  if (isVisible(D))
2038  return true;
2039  assert(D->isExternallyDeclarable() &&
2040  "should not have hidden, non-externally-declarable result here");
2041  }
2042 
2043  // This function is called once "New" is essentially complete, but before a
2044  // previous declaration is attached. We can't query the linkage of "New" in
2045  // general, because attaching the previous declaration can change the
2046  // linkage of New to match the previous declaration.
2047  //
2048  // However, because we've just determined that there is no *visible* prior
2049  // declaration, we can compute the linkage here. There are two possibilities:
2050  //
2051  // * This is not a redeclaration; it's safe to compute the linkage now.
2052  //
2053  // * This is a redeclaration of a prior declaration that is externally
2054  // redeclarable. In that case, the linkage of the declaration is not
2055  // changed by attaching the prior declaration, because both are externally
2056  // declarable (and thus ExternalLinkage or VisibleNoLinkage).
2057  //
2058  // FIXME: This is subtle and fragile.
2059  return New->isExternallyDeclarable();
2060 }
2061 
2062 /// Retrieve the visible declaration corresponding to D, if any.
2063 ///
2064 /// This routine determines whether the declaration D is visible in the current
2065 /// module, with the current imports. If not, it checks whether any
2066 /// redeclaration of D is visible, and if so, returns that declaration.
2067 ///
2068 /// \returns D, or a visible previous declaration of D, whichever is more recent
2069 /// and visible. If no declaration of D is visible, returns null.
2070 static NamedDecl *findAcceptableDecl(Sema &SemaRef, NamedDecl *D,
2071  unsigned IDNS) {
2072  assert(!LookupResult::isAvailableForLookup(SemaRef, D) && "not in slow case");
2073 
2074  for (auto *RD : D->redecls()) {
2075  // Don't bother with extra checks if we already know this one isn't visible.
2076  if (RD == D)
2077  continue;
2078 
2079  auto ND = cast<NamedDecl>(RD);
2080  // FIXME: This is wrong in the case where the previous declaration is not
2081  // visible in the same scope as D. This needs to be done much more
2082  // carefully.
2083  if (ND->isInIdentifierNamespace(IDNS) &&
2084  LookupResult::isAvailableForLookup(SemaRef, ND))
2085  return ND;
2086  }
2087 
2088  return nullptr;
2089 }

2092  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Module *> *Modules) {
2093  assert(!isVisible(D) && "not in slow case");
2094  return hasAcceptableDeclarationImpl(
2095  *this, D, Modules, [](const NamedDecl *) { return true; },
2096  Sema::AcceptableKind::Visible);
