4025 namespace {
4026 
4027 class ShadowContextRAII;
4028 
4029 class VisibleDeclsRecord {
4030 public:
4031  /// An entry in the shadow map, which is optimized to store a
4032  /// single declaration (the common case) but can also store a list
4033  /// of declarations.
4034  typedef llvm::TinyPtrVector<NamedDecl*> ShadowMapEntry;
4035 
4036 private:
4037  /// A mapping from declaration names to the declarations that have
4038  /// this name within a particular scope.
4039  typedef llvm::DenseMap<DeclarationName, ShadowMapEntry> ShadowMap;
4040 
4041  /// A list of shadow maps, which is used to model name hiding.
4042  std::list<ShadowMap> ShadowMaps;
4043 
4044  /// The declaration contexts we have already visited.
4045  llvm::SmallPtrSet<DeclContext *, 8> VisitedContexts;
4046 
4047  friend class ShadowContextRAII;
4048 
4049 public:
4050  /// Determine whether we have already visited this context
4051  /// (and, if not, note that we are going to visit that context now).
4052  bool visitedContext(DeclContext *Ctx) {
4053  return !VisitedContexts.insert(Ctx).second;
4054  }
4055 
4056  bool alreadyVisitedContext(DeclContext *Ctx) {
4057  return VisitedContexts.count(Ctx);
4058  }
4059 
4060  /// Determine whether the given declaration is hidden in the
4061  /// current scope.
4062  ///
4063  /// \returns the declaration that hides the given declaration, or
4064  /// NULL if no such declaration exists.
4065  NamedDecl *checkHidden(NamedDecl *ND);
4066 
4067  /// Add a declaration to the current shadow map.
4068  void add(NamedDecl *ND) {
4069  ShadowMaps.back()[ND->getDeclName()].push_back(ND);
4070  }
4071 };
4072 
4073 /// RAII object that records when we've entered a shadow context.
4074 class ShadowContextRAII {
4075  VisibleDeclsRecord &Visible;
4076 
4077  typedef VisibleDeclsRecord::ShadowMap ShadowMap;
4078 
4079 public:
4080  ShadowContextRAII(VisibleDeclsRecord &Visible) : Visible(Visible) {
4081  Visible.ShadowMaps.emplace_back();
4082  }
4083 
4084  ~ShadowContextRAII() {
4085  Visible.ShadowMaps.pop_back();
4086  }
4087 };
4088 
4089 } // end anonymous namespace
4090 
4091 NamedDecl *VisibleDeclsRecord::checkHidden(NamedDecl *ND) {
4092  unsigned IDNS = ND->getIdentifierNamespace();
4093  std::list<ShadowMap>::reverse_iterator SM = ShadowMaps.rbegin();
4094  for (std::list<ShadowMap>::reverse_iterator SMEnd = ShadowMaps.rend();
4095  SM != SMEnd; ++SM) {
4096  ShadowMap::iterator Pos = SM->find(ND->getDeclName());
4097  if (Pos == SM->end())
4098  continue;
4099 
4100  for (auto *D : Pos->second) {
4101  // A tag declaration does not hide a non-tag declaration.
4102  if (D->hasTagIdentifierNamespace() &&
4103  (IDNS & (Decl::IDNS_Member | Decl::IDNS_Ordinary |
4104  Decl::IDNS_ObjCProtocol)))
4105  continue;
4106 
4107  // Protocols are in distinct namespaces from everything else.
4108  if (((D->getIdentifierNamespace() & Decl::IDNS_ObjCProtocol)
4109  || (IDNS & Decl::IDNS_ObjCProtocol)) &&
4110  D->getIdentifierNamespace() != IDNS)
4111  continue;
4112 
4113  // Functions and function templates in the same scope overload
4114  // rather than hide. FIXME: Look for hiding based on function
4115  // signatures!
4116  if (D->getUnderlyingDecl()->isFunctionOrFunctionTemplate() &&
4117  ND->getUnderlyingDecl()->isFunctionOrFunctionTemplate() &&
4118  SM == ShadowMaps.rbegin())
4119  continue;
4120 
4121  // A shadow declaration that's created by a resolved using declaration
4122  // is not hidden by the same using declaration.
4123  if (isa<UsingShadowDecl>(ND) && isa<UsingDecl>(D) &&
4124  cast<UsingShadowDecl>(ND)->getIntroducer() == D)
4125  continue;
4126 
4127  // We've found a declaration that hides this one.
4128  return D;
4129  }
4130  }
4131 
4132  return nullptr;
4133 }
4134 
4135 namespace {
4136 class LookupVisibleHelper {
4137 public:
4138  LookupVisibleHelper(VisibleDeclConsumer &Consumer, bool IncludeDependentBases,
4139  bool LoadExternal)
4140  : Consumer(Consumer), IncludeDependentBases(IncludeDependentBases),
4141  LoadExternal(LoadExternal) {}
4142 
4143  void lookupVisibleDecls(Sema &SemaRef, Scope *S, Sema::LookupNameKind Kind,
4144  bool IncludeGlobalScope) {
4145  // Determine the set of using directives available during
4146  // unqualified name lookup.
4147  Scope *Initial = S;
4148  UnqualUsingDirectiveSet UDirs(SemaRef);
4149  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
4150  // Find the first namespace or translation-unit scope.
4151  while (S && !isNamespaceOrTranslationUnitScope(S))
4152  S = S->getParent();
4153 
4154  UDirs.visitScopeChain(Initial, S);
4155  }
4156  UDirs.done();
4157 
4158  // Look for visible declarations.
4159  LookupResult Result(SemaRef, DeclarationName(), SourceLocation(), Kind);
4160  Result.setAllowHidden(Consumer.includeHiddenDecls());
4161  if (!IncludeGlobalScope)
4162  Visited.visitedContext(SemaRef.getASTContext().getTranslationUnitDecl());
4163  ShadowContextRAII Shadow(Visited);
4164  lookupInScope(Initial, Result, UDirs);
4165  }
4166 
4167  void lookupVisibleDecls(Sema &SemaRef, DeclContext *Ctx,
4168  Sema::LookupNameKind Kind, bool IncludeGlobalScope) {
4169  LookupResult Result(SemaRef, DeclarationName(), SourceLocation(), Kind);
4170  Result.setAllowHidden(Consumer.includeHiddenDecls());
4171  if (!IncludeGlobalScope)
4172  Visited.visitedContext(SemaRef.getASTContext().getTranslationUnitDecl());
4173 
4174  ShadowContextRAII Shadow(Visited);
4175  lookupInDeclContext(Ctx, Result, /*QualifiedNameLookup=*/true,
4176  /*InBaseClass=*/false);
4177  }
4178 
4179 private:
4180  void lookupInDeclContext(DeclContext *Ctx, LookupResult &Result,
4181  bool QualifiedNameLookup, bool InBaseClass) {
4182  if (!Ctx)
4183  return;
4184 
4185  // Make sure we don't visit the same context twice.
4186  if (Visited.visitedContext(Ctx->getPrimaryContext()))
4187  return;
4188 
4189  Consumer.EnteredContext(Ctx);
4190 
4191  // Outside C++, lookup results for the TU live on identifiers.
4192  if (isa<TranslationUnitDecl>(Ctx) &&
4193  !Result.getSema().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
4194  auto &S = Result.getSema();
4195  auto &Idents = S.Context.Idents;
4196 
4197  // Ensure all external identifiers are in the identifier table.
4198  if (LoadExternal)
4199  if (IdentifierInfoLookup *External =
4200  Idents.getExternalIdentifierLookup()) {
4201  std::unique_ptr<IdentifierIterator> Iter(External->getIdentifiers());
4202  for (StringRef Name = Iter->Next(); !Name.empty();
4203  Name = Iter->Next())
4204  Idents.get(Name);
4205  }
4206 
4207  // Walk all lookup results in the TU for each identifier.
4208  for (const auto &Ident : Idents) {
4209  for (auto I = S.IdResolver.begin(Ident.getValue()),
4210  E = S.IdResolver.end();
4211  I != E; ++I) {
4212  if (S.IdResolver.isDeclInScope(*I, Ctx)) {
4213  if (NamedDecl *ND = Result.getAcceptableDecl(*I)) {
4214  Consumer.FoundDecl(ND, Visited.checkHidden(ND), Ctx, InBaseClass);
4215  Visited.add(ND);
4216  }
4217  }
4218  }
4219  }
4220 
4221  return;
4222  }
4223 
4224  if (CXXRecordDecl *Class = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Ctx))
4225  Result.getSema().ForceDeclarationOfImplicitMembers(Class);
4226 
4227  llvm::SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 4> DeclsToVisit;
4228  // We sometimes skip loading namespace-level results (they tend to be huge).
4229  bool Load = LoadExternal ||
4230  !(isa<TranslationUnitDecl>(Ctx) || isa<NamespaceDecl>(Ctx));
4231  // Enumerate all of the results in this context.
4232  for (DeclContextLookupResult R :
4233  Load ? Ctx->lookups()
4234  : Ctx->noload_lookups(/*PreserveInternalState=*/false))
4235  for (auto *D : R)
4236  // Rather than visit immediately, we put ND into a vector and visit
4237  // all decls, in order, outside of this loop. The reason is that
4238  // Consumer.FoundDecl() and LookupResult::getAcceptableDecl(D)
4239  // may invalidate the iterators used in the two
4240  // loops above.
4241  DeclsToVisit.push_back(D);
4242 
4243  for (auto *D : DeclsToVisit)
4244  if (auto *ND = Result.getAcceptableDecl(D)) {
4245  Consumer.FoundDecl(ND, Visited.checkHidden(ND), Ctx, InBaseClass);
4246  Visited.add(ND);
4247  }
4248 
4249  DeclsToVisit.clear();
4250 
4251  // Traverse using directives for qualified name lookup.
4252  if (QualifiedNameLookup) {
4253  ShadowContextRAII Shadow(Visited);
4254  for (auto *I : Ctx->using_directives()) {
4255  if (!Result.getSema().isVisible(I))
4256  continue;
4257  lookupInDeclContext(I->getNominatedNamespace(), Result,
4258  QualifiedNameLookup, InBaseClass);
4259  }
4260  }
4261 
4262  // Traverse the contexts of inherited C++ classes.
4263  if (CXXRecordDecl *Record = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Ctx)) {
4264  if (!Record->hasDefinition())
4265  return;
4266 
4267  for (const auto &B : Record->bases()) {
4268  QualType BaseType = B.getType();
4269 
4270  RecordDecl *RD;
4271  if (BaseType->isDependentType()) {
4272  if (!IncludeDependentBases) {
4273  // Don't look into dependent bases, because name lookup can't look
4274  // there anyway.
4275  continue;
4276  }
4277  const auto *TST = BaseType->getAs<TemplateSpecializationType>();
4278  if (!TST)
4279  continue;
4280  TemplateName TN = TST->getTemplateName();
4281  const auto *TD =
4282  dyn_cast_or_null<ClassTemplateDecl>(TN.getAsTemplateDecl());
4283  if (!TD)
4284  continue;
4285  RD = TD->getTemplatedDecl();
4286  } else {
4287  const auto *Record = BaseType->getAs<RecordType>();
4288  if (!Record)
4289  continue;
4290  RD = Record->getDecl();
4291  }
4292 
4293  // FIXME: It would be nice to be able to determine whether referencing
4294  // a particular member would be ambiguous. For example, given
4295  //
4296  // struct A { int member; };
4297  // struct B { int member; };
4298  // struct C : A, B { };
4299  //
4300  // void f(C *c) { c->### }
4301  //
4302  // accessing 'member' would result in an ambiguity. However, we
4303  // could be smart enough to qualify the member with the base
4304  // class, e.g.,
4305  //
4306  // c->B::member
4307  //
4308  // or
4309  //
4310  // c->A::member
4311 
4312  // Find results in this base class (and its bases).
4313  ShadowContextRAII Shadow(Visited);
4314  lookupInDeclContext(RD, Result, QualifiedNameLookup,
4315  /*InBaseClass=*/true);
4316  }
4317  }
4318 
4319  // Traverse the contexts of Objective-C classes.
4320  if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *IFace = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(Ctx)) {
4321  // Traverse categories.
4322  for (auto *Cat : IFace->visible_categories()) {
4323  ShadowContextRAII Shadow(Visited);
4324  lookupInDeclContext(Cat, Result, QualifiedNameLookup,
4325  /*InBaseClass=*/false);
4326  }
4327 
4328  // Traverse protocols.
4329  for (auto *I : IFace->all_referenced_protocols()) {
4330  ShadowContextRAII Shadow(Visited);
4331  lookupInDeclContext(I, Result, QualifiedNameLookup,
4332  /*InBaseClass=*/false);
4333  }
4334 
4335  // Traverse the superclass.
4336  if (IFace->getSuperClass()) {
4337  ShadowContextRAII Shadow(Visited);
4338  lookupInDeclContext(IFace->getSuperClass(), Result, QualifiedNameLookup,
4339  /*InBaseClass=*/true);
4340  }
4341 
4342  // If there is an implementation, traverse it. We do this to find
4343  // synthesized ivars.
4344  if (IFace->getImplementation()) {
4345  ShadowContextRAII Shadow(Visited);
4346  lookupInDeclContext(IFace->getImplementation(), Result,
4347  QualifiedNameLookup, InBaseClass);
4348  }
4349  } else if (ObjCProtocolDecl *Protocol = dyn_cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(Ctx)) {
4350  for (auto *I : Protocol->protocols()) {
4351  ShadowContextRAII Shadow(Visited);
4352  lookupInDeclContext(I, Result, QualifiedNameLookup,
4353  /*InBaseClass=*/false);
4354  }
4355  } else if (ObjCCategoryDecl *Category = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(Ctx)) {
4356  for (auto *I : Category->protocols()) {
4357  ShadowContextRAII Shadow(Visited);
4358  lookupInDeclContext(I, Result, QualifiedNameLookup,
4359  /*InBaseClass=*/false);
4360  }
4361 
4362  // If there is an implementation, traverse it.
4363  if (Category->getImplementation()) {
4364  ShadowContextRAII Shadow(Visited);
4365  lookupInDeclContext(Category->getImplementation(), Result,
4366  QualifiedNameLookup, /*InBaseClass=*/true);
4367  }
4368  }
4369  }
4370 
4371  void lookupInScope(Scope *S, LookupResult &Result,
4372  UnqualUsingDirectiveSet &UDirs) {
4373  // No clients run in this mode and it's not supported. Please add tests and
4374  // remove the assertion if you start relying on it.
4375  assert(!IncludeDependentBases && "Unsupported flag for lookupInScope");
4376 
4377  if (!S)
4378  return;
4379 
4380  if (!S->getEntity() ||
4381  (!S->getParent() && !Visited.alreadyVisitedContext(S->getEntity())) ||
4382  (S->getEntity())->isFunctionOrMethod()) {
4383  FindLocalExternScope FindLocals(Result);
4384  // Walk through the declarations in this Scope. The consumer might add new
4385  // decls to the scope as part of deserialization, so make a copy first.
4386  SmallVector<Decl *, 8> ScopeDecls(S->decls().begin(), S->decls().end());
4387  for (Decl *D : ScopeDecls) {
4388  if (NamedDecl *ND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(D))
4389  if ((ND = Result.getAcceptableDecl(ND))) {
4390  Consumer.FoundDecl(ND, Visited.checkHidden(ND), nullptr, false);
4391  Visited.add(ND);
4392  }
4393  }
4394  }
4395 
4396  DeclContext *Entity = S->getLookupEntity();
4397  if (Entity) {
4398  // Look into this scope's declaration context, along with any of its
4399  // parent lookup contexts (e.g., enclosing classes), up to the point
4400  // where we hit the context stored in the next outer scope.
4401  DeclContext *OuterCtx = findOuterContext(S);
4402 
4403  for (DeclContext *Ctx = Entity; Ctx && !Ctx->Equals(OuterCtx);
4404  Ctx = Ctx->getLookupParent()) {
4405  if (ObjCMethodDecl *Method = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(Ctx)) {
4406  if (Method->isInstanceMethod()) {
4407  // For instance methods, look for ivars in the method's interface.
4408  LookupResult IvarResult(Result.getSema(), Result.getLookupName(),
4409  Result.getNameLoc(),
4410  Sema::LookupMemberName);
4411  if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *IFace = Method->getClassInterface()) {
4412  lookupInDeclContext(IFace, IvarResult,
4413  /*QualifiedNameLookup=*/false,
4414  /*InBaseClass=*/false);
4415  }
4416  }
4417 
4418  // We've already performed all of the name lookup that we need
4419  // to for Objective-C methods; the next context will be the
4420  // outer scope.
4421  break;
4422  }
4423 
4424  if (Ctx->isFunctionOrMethod())
4425  continue;
4426 
4427  lookupInDeclContext(Ctx, Result, /*QualifiedNameLookup=*/false,
4428  /*InBaseClass=*/false);
4429  }
4430  } else if (!S->getParent()) {
4431  // Look into the translation unit scope. We walk through the translation
4432  // unit's declaration context, because the Scope itself won't have all of
4433  // the declarations if we loaded a precompiled header.
4434  // FIXME: We would like the translation unit's Scope object to point to
4435  // the translation unit, so we don't need this special "if" branch.
4436  // However, doing so would force the normal C++ name-lookup code to look
4437  // into the translation unit decl when the IdentifierInfo chains would
4438  // suffice. Once we fix that problem (which is part of a more general
4439  // "don't look in DeclContexts unless we have to" optimization), we can
4440  // eliminate this.
4441  Entity = Result.getSema().Context.getTranslationUnitDecl();
4442  lookupInDeclContext(Entity, Result, /*QualifiedNameLookup=*/false,
4443  /*InBaseClass=*/false);
4444  }
4445 
4446  if (Entity) {
4447  // Lookup visible declarations in any namespaces found by using
4448  // directives.
4449  for (const UnqualUsingEntry &UUE : UDirs.getNamespacesFor(Entity))
4450  lookupInDeclContext(
4451  const_cast<DeclContext *>(UUE.getNominatedNamespace()), Result,
4452  /*QualifiedNameLookup=*/false,
4453  /*InBaseClass=*/false);
4454  }
4455 
4456  // Lookup names in the parent scope.
4457  ShadowContextRAII Shadow(Visited);
4458  lookupInScope(S->getParent(), Result, UDirs);
4459  }
4460 
4461 private:
4462  VisibleDeclsRecord Visited;
4463  VisibleDeclConsumer &Consumer;
4464  bool IncludeDependentBases;
4465  bool LoadExternal;
4466 };
4467 } // namespace
4468 
4469 void Sema::LookupVisibleDecls(Scope *S, LookupNameKind Kind,
4470  VisibleDeclConsumer &Consumer,
4471  bool IncludeGlobalScope, bool LoadExternal) {
4472  LookupVisibleHelper H(Consumer, /*IncludeDependentBases=*/false,
4473  LoadExternal);
4474  H.lookupVisibleDecls(*this, S, Kind, IncludeGlobalScope);
4475 }

4477 void Sema::LookupVisibleDecls(DeclContext *Ctx, LookupNameKind Kind,
4478  VisibleDeclConsumer &Consumer,
4479  bool IncludeGlobalScope,
4480  bool IncludeDependentBases, bool LoadExternal) {
4481  LookupVisibleHelper H(Consumer, IncludeDependentBases, LoadExternal);
4482  H.lookupVisibleDecls(*this, Ctx, Kind, IncludeGlobalScope);
4483 }
4484 
4485 /// LookupOrCreateLabel - Do a name lookup of a label with the specified name.
4486 /// If GnuLabelLoc is a valid source location, then this is a definition
4487 /// of an __label__ label name, otherwise it is a normal label definition
4488 /// or use.
4489 LabelDecl *Sema::LookupOrCreateLabel(IdentifierInfo *II, SourceLocation Loc,
4490  SourceLocation GnuLabelLoc) {
4491  // Do a lookup to see if we have a label with this name already.
4492  NamedDecl *Res = nullptr;
4493 
4494  if (GnuLabelLoc.isValid()) {
4495  // Local label definitions always shadow existing labels.
4496  Res = LabelDecl::Create(Context, CurContext, Loc, II, GnuLabelLoc);
4497  Scope *S = CurScope;
4498  PushOnScopeChains(Res, S, true);
4499  return cast<LabelDecl>(Res);
4500  }
4501 
4502  // Not a GNU local label.
4503  Res = LookupSingleName(CurScope, II, Loc, LookupLabel,
4504  RedeclarationKind::NotForRedeclaration);
4505  // If we found a label, check to see if it is in the same context as us.
4506  // When in a Block, we don't want to reuse a label in an enclosing function.
4507  if (Res && Res->getDeclContext() != CurContext)
4508  Res = nullptr;
4509  if (!Res) {
4510  // If not forward referenced or defined already, create the backing decl.
4511  Res = LabelDecl::Create(Context, CurContext, Loc, II);
4512  Scope *S = CurScope->getFnParent();
4513  assert(S && "Not in a function?");
4514  PushOnScopeChains(Res, S, true);
4515  }
4516  return cast<LabelDecl>(Res);
4517 }

4519 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4520 // Typo correction
4521 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4522 
4523 static bool isCandidateViable(CorrectionCandidateCallback &CCC,
4524  TypoCorrection &Candidate) {
4525  Candidate.setCallbackDistance(CCC.RankCandidate(Candidate));
4526  return Candidate.getEditDistance(false) != TypoCorrection::InvalidDistance;
4527 }
4528 
4529 static void LookupPotentialTypoResult(Sema &SemaRef,
4530  LookupResult &Res,
4531  IdentifierInfo *Name,
4532  Scope *S, CXXScopeSpec *SS,
4533  DeclContext *MemberContext,
4534  bool EnteringContext,
4535  bool isObjCIvarLookup,
4536  bool FindHidden);
4537 
4538 /// Check whether the declarations found for a typo correction are
4539 /// visible. Set the correction's RequiresImport flag to true if none of the
4540 /// declarations are visible, false otherwise.
4541 static void checkCorrectionVisibility(Sema &SemaRef, TypoCorrection &TC) {
4542  TypoCorrection::decl_iterator DI = TC.begin(), DE = TC.end();
4543 
4544  for (/**/; DI != DE; ++DI)
4545  if (!LookupResult::isVisible(SemaRef, *DI))
4546  break;
4547  // No filtering needed if all decls are visible.
4548  if (DI == DE) {
4549  TC.setRequiresImport(false);
4550  return;
4551  }
4552 
4553  llvm::SmallVector<NamedDecl*, 4> NewDecls(TC.begin(), DI);
4554  bool AnyVisibleDecls = !NewDecls.empty();
4555 
4556  for (/**/; DI != DE; ++DI) {
4557  if (LookupResult::isVisible(SemaRef, *DI)) {
4558  if (!AnyVisibleDecls) {
4559  // Found a visible decl, discard all hidden ones.
4560  AnyVisibleDecls = true;
4561  NewDecls.clear();
4562  }
4563  NewDecls.push_back(*DI);
4564  } else if (!AnyVisibleDecls && !(*DI)->isModulePrivate())
4565  NewDecls.push_back(*DI);
4566  }
4567 
4568  if (NewDecls.empty())
4569  TC = TypoCorrection();
4570  else {
4571  TC.setCorrectionDecls(NewDecls);
4572  TC.setRequiresImport(!AnyVisibleDecls);
4573  }
4574 }
4575 
4576 // Fill the supplied vector with the IdentifierInfo pointers for each piece of
4577 // the given NestedNameSpecifier (i.e. given a NestedNameSpecifier "foo::bar::",
4578 // fill the vector with the IdentifierInfo pointers for "foo" and "bar").
4579 static void getNestedNameSpecifierIdentifiers(
4580  NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
4581  SmallVectorImpl<const IdentifierInfo*> &Identifiers) {
4582  if (NestedNameSpecifier *Prefix = NNS->getPrefix())
4583  getNestedNameSpecifierIdentifiers(Prefix, Identifiers);
4584  else
4585  Identifiers.clear();
4586 
4587  const IdentifierInfo *II = nullptr;
4588 
4589  switch (NNS->getKind()) {
4590  case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
4591  II = NNS->getAsIdentifier();
4592  break;
4593 
4594  case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
4595  if (NNS->getAsNamespace()->isAnonymousNamespace())
4596  return;
4597  II = NNS->getAsNamespace()->getIdentifier();
4598  break;
4599 
4600  case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
4601  II = NNS->getAsNamespaceAlias()->getIdentifier();
4602  break;
4603 
4604  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate:
4605  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
4606  II = QualType(NNS->getAsType(), 0).getBaseTypeIdentifier();
4607  break;
4608 
4609  case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
4610  case NestedNameSpecifier::Super:
4611  return;
4612  }
4613 
4614  if (II)
4615  Identifiers.push_back(II);
4616 }
4617 
4618 void TypoCorrectionConsumer::FoundDecl(NamedDecl *ND, NamedDecl *Hiding,
4619  DeclContext *Ctx, bool InBaseClass) {
4620  // Don't consider hidden names for typo correction.
4621  if (Hiding)
4622  return;
4623 
4624  // Only consider entities with identifiers for names, ignoring
4625  // special names (constructors, overloaded operators, selectors,
4626  // etc.).
4627  IdentifierInfo *Name = ND->getIdentifier();
4628  if (!Name)
4629  return;
4630 
4631  // Only consider visible declarations and declarations from modules with
4632  // names that exactly match.
4633  if (!LookupResult::isVisible(SemaRef, ND) && Name != Typo)
4634  return;
4635 
4636  FoundName(Name->getName());
4637 }
4638 
4639 void TypoCorrectionConsumer::FoundName(StringRef Name) {
4640  // Compute the edit distance between the typo and the name of this
4641  // entity, and add the identifier to the list of results.
4642  addName(Name, nullptr);
4643 }
4644 
4645 void TypoCorrectionConsumer::addKeywordResult(StringRef Keyword) {
4646  // Compute the edit distance between the typo and this keyword,
4647  // and add the keyword to the list of results.
4648  addName(Keyword, nullptr, nullptr, true);
4649 }
4650 
4651 void TypoCorrectionConsumer::addName(StringRef Name, NamedDecl *ND,
4652  NestedNameSpecifier *NNS, bool isKeyword) {
4653  // Use a simple length-based heuristic to determine the minimum possible
4654  // edit distance. If the minimum isn't good enough, bail out early.
4655  StringRef TypoStr = Typo->getName();
4656  unsigned MinED = abs((int)Name.size() - (int)TypoStr.size());
4657  if (MinED && TypoStr.size() / MinED < 3)
4658  return;
4659 
4660  // Compute an upper bound on the allowable edit distance, so that the
4661  // edit-distance algorithm can short-circuit.
4662  unsigned UpperBound = (TypoStr.size() + 2) / 3;
4663  unsigned ED = TypoStr.edit_distance(Name, true, UpperBound);
4664  if (ED > UpperBound) return;
4665 
4666  TypoCorrection TC(&SemaRef.Context.Idents.get(Name), ND, NNS, ED);
4667  if (isKeyword) TC.makeKeyword();
4668  TC.setCorrectionRange(nullptr, Result.getLookupNameInfo());
4669  addCorrection(TC);
4670 }
4671 
4672 static const unsigned MaxTypoDistanceResultSets = 5;
4673 
4674 void TypoCorrectionConsumer::addCorrection(TypoCorrection Correction) {
4675  StringRef TypoStr = Typo->getName();
4676  StringRef Name = Correction.getCorrectionAsIdentifierInfo()->getName();
4677 
4678  // For very short typos, ignore potential corrections that have a different
4679  // base identifier from the typo or which have a normalized edit distance
4680  // longer than the typo itself.
4681  if (TypoStr.size() < 3 &&
4682  (Name != TypoStr || Correction.getEditDistance(true) > TypoStr.size()))
4683  return;
4684 
4685  // If the correction is resolved but is not viable, ignore it.
4686  if (Correction.isResolved()) {
4687  checkCorrectionVisibility(SemaRef, Correction);
4688  if (!Correction || !isCandidateViable(*CorrectionValidator, Correction))
4689  return;
4690  }
4691 
4692  TypoResultList &CList =
4693  CorrectionResults[Correction.getEditDistance(false)][Name];
4694 
4695  if (!CList.empty() && !CList.back().isResolved())
4696  CList.pop_back();
4697  if (NamedDecl *NewND = Correction.getCorrectionDecl()) {
4698  auto RI = llvm::find_if(CList, [NewND](const TypoCorrection &TypoCorr) {
4699  return TypoCorr.getCorrectionDecl() == NewND;
4700  });
4701  if (RI != CList.end()) {
4702  // The Correction refers to a decl already in the list. No insertion is
4703  // necessary and all further cases will return.
4704 
4705  auto IsDeprecated = [](Decl *D) {
4706  while (D) {
4707  if (D->isDeprecated())
4708  return true;
4709  D = llvm::dyn_cast_or_null<NamespaceDecl>(D->getDeclContext());
4710  }
4711  return false;
4712  };
4713 
4714  // Prefer non deprecated Corrections over deprecated and only then
4715  // sort using an alphabetical order.
4716  std::pair<bool, std::string> NewKey = {
4717  IsDeprecated(Correction.getFoundDecl()),
4718  Correction.getAsString(SemaRef.getLangOpts())};
4719 
4720  std::pair<bool, std::string> PrevKey = {
4721  IsDeprecated(RI->getFoundDecl()),
4722  RI->getAsString(SemaRef.getLangOpts())};
4723 
4724  if (NewKey < PrevKey)
4725  *RI = Correction;
4726  return;
4727  }
4728  }
4729  if (CList.empty() || Correction.isResolved())
4730  CList.push_back(Correction);
4731 
4732  while (CorrectionResults.size() > MaxTypoDistanceResultSets)
4733  CorrectionResults.erase(std::prev(CorrectionResults.end()));
4734 }
4735 
4736 void TypoCorrectionConsumer::addNamespaces(
4737  const llvm::MapVector<NamespaceDecl *, bool> &KnownNamespaces) {
4738  SearchNamespaces = true;
4739 
4740  for (auto KNPair : KnownNamespaces)
4741  Namespaces.addNameSpecifier(KNPair.first);
4742 
4743  bool SSIsTemplate = false;
4744  if (NestedNameSpecifier *NNS =
4745  (SS && SS->isValid()) ? SS->getScopeRep() : nullptr) {
4746  if (const Type *T = NNS->getAsType())
4747  SSIsTemplate = T->getTypeClass() == Type::TemplateSpecialization;
4748  }
4749  // Do not transform this into an iterator-based loop. The loop body can
4750  // trigger the creation of further types (through lazy deserialization) and
4751  // invalid iterators into this list.
4752  auto &Types = SemaRef.getASTContext().getTypes();
4753  for (unsigned I = 0; I != Types.size(); ++I) {
4754  const auto *TI = Types[I];
4755  if (CXXRecordDecl *CD = TI->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
4756  CD = CD->getCanonicalDecl();
4757  if (!CD->isDependentType() && !CD->isAnonymousStructOrUnion() &&
4758  !CD->isUnion() && CD->getIdentifier() &&
4759  (SSIsTemplate || !isa<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(CD)) &&
4760  (CD->isBeingDefined() || CD->isCompleteDefinition()))
4761  Namespaces.addNameSpecifier(CD);
4762  }
4763  }
4764 }
4765 
4766 const TypoCorrection &TypoCorrectionConsumer::getNextCorrection() {
4767  if (++CurrentTCIndex < ValidatedCorrections.size())
4768  return ValidatedCorrections[CurrentTCIndex];
4769 
4770  CurrentTCIndex = ValidatedCorrections.size();
4771  while (!CorrectionResults.empty()) {
4772  auto DI = CorrectionResults.begin();
4773  if (DI->second.empty()) {
4774  CorrectionResults.erase(DI);
4775  continue;
4776  }
4777 
4778  auto RI = DI->second.begin();
4779  if (RI->second.empty()) {
4780  DI->second.erase(RI);
4781  performQualifiedLookups();
4782  continue;
4783  }
4784 
4785  TypoCorrection TC = RI->second.pop_back_val();
4786  if (TC.isResolved() || TC.requiresImport() || resolveCorrection(TC)) {
4787  ValidatedCorrections.push_back(TC);
4788  return ValidatedCorrections[CurrentTCIndex];
4789  }
4790  }
4791  return ValidatedCorrections[0]; // The empty correction.
4792 }
4793 
4794 bool TypoCorrectionConsumer::resolveCorrection(TypoCorrection &Candidate) {
4795  IdentifierInfo *Name = Candidate.getCorrectionAsIdentifierInfo();
4796  DeclContext *TempMemberContext = MemberContext;
4797  CXXScopeSpec *TempSS = SS.get();
4798 retry_lookup:
4799  LookupPotentialTypoResult(SemaRef, Result, Name, S, TempSS, TempMemberContext,
4800  EnteringContext,
4801  CorrectionValidator->IsObjCIvarLookup,
4802  Name == Typo && !Candidate.WillReplaceSpecifier());
4803  switch (Result.getResultKind()) {
4804  case LookupResult::NotFound:
4805  case LookupResult::NotFoundInCurrentInstantiation:
4806  case LookupResult::FoundUnresolvedValue:
4807  if (TempSS) {
4808  // Immediately retry the lookup without the given CXXScopeSpec
4809  TempSS = nullptr;
4810  Candidate.WillReplaceSpecifier(true);
4811  goto retry_lookup;
4812  }
4813  if (TempMemberContext) {
4814  if (SS && !TempSS)
4815  TempSS = SS.get();
4816  TempMemberContext = nullptr;
4817  goto retry_lookup;
4818  }
4819  if (SearchNamespaces)
4820  QualifiedResults.push_back(Candidate);
4821  break;
4822 
4823  case LookupResult::Ambiguous:
4824  // We don't deal with ambiguities.
4825  break;
4826 
4827  case LookupResult::Found:
4828  case LookupResult::FoundOverloaded:
4829  // Store all of the Decls for overloaded symbols
4830  for (auto *TRD : Result)
4831  Candidate.addCorrectionDecl(TRD);
4832  checkCorrectionVisibility(SemaRef, Candidate);
4833  if (!isCandidateViable(*CorrectionValidator, Candidate)) {
4834  if (SearchNamespaces)
4835  QualifiedResults.push_back(Candidate);
4836  break;
4837  }
4838  Candidate.setCorrectionRange(SS.get(), Result.getLookupNameInfo());
4839  return true;
4840  }
4841  return false;
4842 }
4843 
4844 void TypoCorrectionConsumer::performQualifiedLookups() {
4845  unsigned TypoLen = Typo->getName().size();
4846  for (const TypoCorrection &QR : QualifiedResults) {
4847  for (const auto &NSI : Namespaces) {
4848  DeclContext *Ctx = NSI.DeclCtx;
4849  const Type *NSType = NSI.NameSpecifier->getAsType();
4850 
4851  // If the current NestedNameSpecifier refers to a class and the
4852  // current correction candidate is the name of that class, then skip
4853  // it as it is unlikely a qualified version of the class' constructor
4854  // is an appropriate correction.
4855  if (CXXRecordDecl *NSDecl = NSType ? NSType->getAsCXXRecordDecl() :
4856  nullptr) {
4857  if (NSDecl->getIdentifier() == QR.getCorrectionAsIdentifierInfo())
4858  continue;
4859  }
4860 
4861  TypoCorrection TC(QR);
4862  TC.ClearCorrectionDecls();
4863  TC.setCorrectionSpecifier(NSI.NameSpecifier);
4864  TC.setQualifierDistance(NSI.EditDistance);
4865  TC.setCallbackDistance(0); // Reset the callback distance
4866 
4867  // If the current correction candidate and namespace combination are
4868  // too far away from the original typo based on the normalized edit
4869  // distance, then skip performing a qualified name lookup.
4870  unsigned TmpED = TC.getEditDistance(true);
4871  if (QR.getCorrectionAsIdentifierInfo() != Typo && TmpED &&
4872  TypoLen / TmpED < 3)
4873  continue;
4874 
4875  Result.clear();
4876  Result.setLookupName(QR.getCorrectionAsIdentifierInfo());
4877  if (!SemaRef.LookupQualifiedName(Result, Ctx))
4878  continue;
4879 
4880  // Any corrections added below will be validated in subsequent
4881  // iterations of the main while() loop over the Consumer's contents.
4882  switch (Result.getResultKind()) {
4883  case LookupResult::Found:
4884  case LookupResult::FoundOverloaded: {
4885  if (SS && SS->isValid()) {
4886  std::string NewQualified = TC.getAsString(SemaRef.getLangOpts());
4887  std::string OldQualified;
4888  llvm::raw_string_ostream OldOStream(OldQualified);
4889  SS->getScopeRep()->print(OldOStream, SemaRef.getPrintingPolicy());
4890  OldOStream << Typo->getName();
4891  // If correction candidate would be an identical written qualified
4892  // identifier, then the existing CXXScopeSpec probably included a
4893  // typedef that didn't get accounted for properly.
4894  if (OldOStream.str() == NewQualified)
4895  break;
4896  }
4897  for (LookupResult::iterator TRD = Result.begin(), TRDEnd = Result.end();
4898  TRD != TRDEnd; ++TRD) {
4899  if (SemaRef.CheckMemberAccess(TC.getCorrectionRange().getBegin(),
4900  NSType ? NSType->getAsCXXRecordDecl()
4901  : nullptr,
4902  TRD.getPair()) == Sema::AR_accessible)
4903  TC.addCorrectionDecl(*TRD);
4904  }
4905  if (TC.isResolved()) {
4906  TC.setCorrectionRange(SS.get(), Result.getLookupNameInfo());
4907  addCorrection(TC);
4908  }
4909  break;
4910  }
4911  case LookupResult::NotFound:
4912  case LookupResult::NotFoundInCurrentInstantiation:
4913  case LookupResult::Ambiguous:
4914  case LookupResult::FoundUnresolvedValue:
4915  break;
4916  }
4917  }
4918  }
4919  QualifiedResults.clear();
4920 }
4921 
4922 TypoCorrectionConsumer::NamespaceSpecifierSet::NamespaceSpecifierSet(
4923  ASTContext &Context, DeclContext *CurContext, CXXScopeSpec *CurScopeSpec)
4924  : Context(Context), CurContextChain(buildContextChain(CurContext)) {
4925  if (NestedNameSpecifier *NNS =
4926  CurScopeSpec ? CurScopeSpec->getScopeRep() : nullptr) {
4927  llvm::raw_string_ostream SpecifierOStream(CurNameSpecifier);
4928  NNS->print(SpecifierOStream, Context.getPrintingPolicy());
4929 
4930  getNestedNameSpecifierIdentifiers(NNS, CurNameSpecifierIdentifiers);
4931  }
4932  // Build the list of identifiers that would be used for an absolute
4933  // (from the global context) NestedNameSpecifier referring to the current
4934  // context.
4935  for (DeclContext *C : llvm::reverse(CurContextChain)) {
4936  if (auto *ND = dyn_cast_or_null<NamespaceDecl>(C))
4937  CurContextIdentifiers.push_back(ND->getIdentifier());
4938  }
4939 
4940  // Add the global context as a NestedNameSpecifier
4941  SpecifierInfo SI = {cast<DeclContext>(Context.getTranslationUnitDecl()),
4942  NestedNameSpecifier::GlobalSpecifier(Context), 1};
4943  DistanceMap[1].push_back(SI);
4944 }
4945 
4946 auto TypoCorrectionConsumer::NamespaceSpecifierSet::buildContextChain(
4947  DeclContext *Start) -> DeclContextList {
4948  assert(Start && "Building a context chain from a null context");
4949  DeclContextList Chain;
4950  for (DeclContext *DC = Start->getPrimaryContext(); DC != nullptr;
4951  DC = DC->getLookupParent()) {
4952  NamespaceDecl *ND = dyn_cast_or_null<NamespaceDecl>(DC);
4953  if (!DC->isInlineNamespace() && !DC->isTransparentContext() &&
4954  !(ND && ND->isAnonymousNamespace()))
4955  Chain.push_back(DC->getPrimaryContext());
4956  }
4957  return Chain;
4958 }
4959 
4960 unsigned
4961 TypoCorrectionConsumer::NamespaceSpecifierSet::buildNestedNameSpecifier(
4962  DeclContextList &DeclChain, NestedNameSpecifier *&NNS) {
4963  unsigned NumSpecifiers = 0;
4964  for (DeclContext *C : llvm::reverse(DeclChain)) {
4965  if (auto *ND = dyn_cast_or_null<NamespaceDecl>(C)) {
4966  NNS = NestedNameSpecifier::Create(Context, NNS, ND);
4967  ++NumSpecifiers;
4968  } else if (auto *RD = dyn_cast_or_null<RecordDecl>(C)) {
4969  NNS = NestedNameSpecifier::Create(Context, NNS, RD->isTemplateDecl(),
4970  RD->getTypeForDecl());
4971  ++NumSpecifiers;
4972  }
4973  }
4974  return NumSpecifiers;
4975 }
4976 
4977 void TypoCorrectionConsumer::NamespaceSpecifierSet::addNameSpecifier(
4978  DeclContext *Ctx) {
4979  NestedNameSpecifier *NNS = nullptr;
4980  unsigned NumSpecifiers = 0;
4981  DeclContextList NamespaceDeclChain(buildContextChain(Ctx));
4982  DeclContextList FullNamespaceDeclChain(NamespaceDeclChain);
4983 
4984  // Eliminate common elements from the two DeclContext chains.
4985  for (DeclContext *C : llvm::reverse(CurContextChain)) {
4986  if (NamespaceDeclChain.empty() || NamespaceDeclChain.back() != C)
4987  break;
4988  NamespaceDeclChain.pop_back();
4989  }
4990 
4991  // Build the NestedNameSpecifier from what is left of the NamespaceDeclChain
4992  NumSpecifiers = buildNestedNameSpecifier(NamespaceDeclChain, NNS);
4993 
4994  // Add an explicit leading '::' specifier if needed.
4995  if (NamespaceDeclChain.empty()) {
4996  // Rebuild the NestedNameSpecifier as a globally-qualified specifier.
4997  NNS = NestedNameSpecifier::GlobalSpecifier(Context);
4998  NumSpecifiers =
4999  buildNestedNameSpecifier(FullNamespaceDeclChain, NNS);
5000  } else if (NamedDecl *ND =
5001  dyn_cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(NamespaceDeclChain.back())) {
5002  IdentifierInfo *Name = ND->getIdentifier();
5003  bool SameNameSpecifier = false;
5004  if (llvm::is_contained(CurNameSpecifierIdentifiers, Name)) {
5005  std::string NewNameSpecifier;
5006  llvm::raw_string_ostream SpecifierOStream(NewNameSpecifier);
5007  SmallVector<const IdentifierInfo *, 4> NewNameSpecifierIdentifiers;
5008  getNestedNameSpecifierIdentifiers(NNS, NewNameSpecifierIdentifiers);
5009  NNS->print(SpecifierOStream, Context.getPrintingPolicy());
5010  SpecifierOStream.flush();
5011  SameNameSpecifier = NewNameSpecifier == CurNameSpecifier;
5012  }
5013  if (SameNameSpecifier || llvm::is_contained(CurContextIdentifiers, Name)) {
5014  // Rebuild the NestedNameSpecifier as a globally-qualified specifier.
5015  NNS = NestedNameSpecifier::GlobalSpecifier(Context);
5016  NumSpecifiers =
5017  buildNestedNameSpecifier(FullNamespaceDeclChain, NNS);
5018  }
5019  }
5020 
5021  // If the built NestedNameSpecifier would be replacing an existing
5022  // NestedNameSpecifier, use the number of component identifiers that
5023  // would need to be changed as the edit distance instead of the number
5024  // of components in the built NestedNameSpecifier.
5025  if (NNS && !CurNameSpecifierIdentifiers.empty()) {
5026  SmallVector<const IdentifierInfo*, 4> NewNameSpecifierIdentifiers;
5027  getNestedNameSpecifierIdentifiers(NNS, NewNameSpecifierIdentifiers);
5028  NumSpecifiers =
5029  llvm::ComputeEditDistance(llvm::ArrayRef(CurNameSpecifierIdentifiers),
5030  llvm::ArrayRef(NewNameSpecifierIdentifiers));
5031  }
5032 
5033  SpecifierInfo SI = {Ctx, NNS, NumSpecifiers};
5034  DistanceMap[NumSpecifiers].push_back(SI);
5035 }
5036 
5037 /// Perform name lookup for a possible result for typo correction.
5038 static void LookupPotentialTypoResult(Sema &SemaRef,
5039  LookupResult &Res,
5040  IdentifierInfo *Name,
5041  Scope *S, CXXScopeSpec *SS,
5042  DeclContext *MemberContext,
5043  bool EnteringContext,
5044  bool isObjCIvarLookup,
5045  bool FindHidden) {
5046  Res.suppressDiagnostics();
5047  Res.clear();
5048  Res.setLookupName(Name);
5049  Res.setAllowHidden(FindHidden);
5050  if (MemberContext) {
5051  if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(MemberContext)) {
5052  if (isObjCIvarLookup) {
5053  if (ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar = Class->lookupInstanceVariable(Name)) {
5054  Res.addDecl(Ivar);
5055  Res.resolveKind();
5056  return;
5057  }
5058  }
5059 
5060  if (ObjCPropertyDecl *Prop = Class->FindPropertyDeclaration(
5061  Name, ObjCPropertyQueryKind::OBJC_PR_query_instance)) {
5062  Res.addDecl(Prop);
5063  Res.resolveKind();
5064  return;
5065  }
5066  }
5067 
5068  SemaRef.LookupQualifiedName(Res, MemberContext);
5069  return;
5070  }
5071 
5072  SemaRef.LookupParsedName(Res, S, SS, /*AllowBuiltinCreation=*/false,
5073  EnteringContext);
5074 
5075  // Fake ivar lookup; this should really be part of
5076  // LookupParsedName.
5077  if (ObjCMethodDecl *Method = SemaRef.getCurMethodDecl()) {
5078  if (Method->isInstanceMethod() && Method->getClassInterface() &&
5079  (Res.empty() ||
5080  (Res.isSingleResult() &&
5081  Res.getFoundDecl()->isDefinedOutsideFunctionOrMethod()))) {
5082  if (ObjCIvarDecl *IV
5083  = Method->getClassInterface()->lookupInstanceVariable(Name)) {
5084  Res.addDecl(IV);
5085  Res.resolveKind();
5086  }
5087  }
5088  }
5089 }
5090 
5091 /// Add keywords to the consumer as possible typo corrections.
5092 static void AddKeywordsToConsumer(Sema &SemaRef,
5093  TypoCorrectionConsumer &Consumer,
5094  Scope *S, CorrectionCandidateCallback &CCC,
5095  bool AfterNestedNameSpecifier) {
5096  if (AfterNestedNameSpecifier) {
5097  // For 'X::', we know exactly which keywords can appear next.
5098  Consumer.addKeywordResult("template");
5099  if (CCC.WantExpressionKeywords)
5100  Consumer.addKeywordResult("operator");
5101  return;
5102  }
5103 
5104  if (CCC.WantObjCSuper)
5105  Consumer.addKeywordResult("super");
5106 
5107  if (CCC.WantTypeSpecifiers) {
5108  // Add type-specifier keywords to the set of results.
5109  static const char *const CTypeSpecs[] = {
5110  "char", "const", "double", "enum", "float", "int", "long", "short",
5111  "signed", "struct", "union", "unsigned", "void", "volatile",
5112  "_Complex", "_Imaginary",
5113  // storage-specifiers as well
5114  "extern", "inline", "static", "typedef"
5115  };
5116 
5117  for (const auto *CTS : CTypeSpecs)
5118  Consumer.addKeywordResult(CTS);
5119 
5120  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().C99)
5121  Consumer.addKeywordResult("restrict");
5122  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().Bool || SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
5123  Consumer.addKeywordResult("bool");
5124  else if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().C99)
5125  Consumer.addKeywordResult("_Bool");
5126 
5127  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5128  Consumer.addKeywordResult("class");
5129  Consumer.addKeywordResult("typename");
5130  Consumer.addKeywordResult("wchar_t");
5131 
5132  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
5133  Consumer.addKeywordResult("char16_t");
5134  Consumer.addKeywordResult("char32_t");
5135  Consumer.addKeywordResult("constexpr");
5136  Consumer.addKeywordResult("decltype");
5137  Consumer.addKeywordResult("thread_local");
5138  }
5139  }
5140 
5141  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().GNUKeywords)
5142  Consumer.addKeywordResult("typeof");
5143  } else if (CCC.WantFunctionLikeCasts) {
5144  static const char *const CastableTypeSpecs[] = {
5145  "char", "double", "float", "int", "long", "short",
5146  "signed", "unsigned", "void"
5147  };
5148  for (auto *kw : CastableTypeSpecs)
5149  Consumer.addKeywordResult(kw);
5150  }
5151 
5152  if (CCC.WantCXXNamedCasts && SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5153  Consumer.addKeywordResult("const_cast");
5154  Consumer.addKeywordResult("dynamic_cast");
5155  Consumer.addKeywordResult("reinterpret_cast");
5156  Consumer.addKeywordResult("static_cast");
5157  }
5158 
5159  if (CCC.WantExpressionKeywords) {
5160  Consumer.addKeywordResult("sizeof");
5161  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().Bool || SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5162  Consumer.addKeywordResult("false");
5163  Consumer.addKeywordResult("true");
5164  }
5165 
5166  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5167  static const char *const CXXExprs[] = {
5168  "delete", "new", "operator", "throw", "typeid"
5169  };
5170  for (const auto *CE : CXXExprs)
5171  Consumer.addKeywordResult(CE);
5172 
5173  if (isa<CXXMethodDecl>(SemaRef.CurContext) &&
5174  cast<CXXMethodDecl>(SemaRef.CurContext)->isInstance())
5175  Consumer.addKeywordResult("this");
5176 
5177  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
5178  Consumer.addKeywordResult("alignof");
5179  Consumer.addKeywordResult("nullptr");
5180  }
5181  }
5182 
5183  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().C11) {
5184  // FIXME: We should not suggest _Alignof if the alignof macro
5185  // is present.
5186  Consumer.addKeywordResult("_Alignof");
5187  }
5188  }
5189 
5190  if (CCC.WantRemainingKeywords) {
5191  if (SemaRef.getCurFunctionOrMethodDecl() || SemaRef.getCurBlock()) {
5192  // Statements.
5193  static const char *const CStmts[] = {
5194  "do", "else", "for", "goto", "if", "return", "switch", "while" };
5195  for (const auto *CS : CStmts)
5196  Consumer.addKeywordResult(CS);
5197 
5198  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5199  Consumer.addKeywordResult("catch");
5200  Consumer.addKeywordResult("try");
5201  }
5202 
5203  if (S && S->getBreakParent())
5204  Consumer.addKeywordResult("break");
5205 
5206  if (S && S->getContinueParent())
5207  Consumer.addKeywordResult("continue");
5208 
5209  if (SemaRef.getCurFunction() &&
5210  !SemaRef.getCurFunction()->SwitchStack.empty()) {
5211  Consumer.addKeywordResult("case");
5212  Consumer.addKeywordResult("default");
5213  }
5214  } else {
5215  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5216  Consumer.addKeywordResult("namespace");
5217  Consumer.addKeywordResult("template");
5218  }
5219 
5220  if (S && S->isClassScope()) {
5221  Consumer.addKeywordResult("explicit");
5222  Consumer.addKeywordResult("friend");
5223  Consumer.addKeywordResult("mutable");
5224  Consumer.addKeywordResult("private");
5225  Consumer.addKeywordResult("protected");
5226  Consumer.addKeywordResult("public");
5227  Consumer.addKeywordResult("virtual");
5228  }
5229  }
5230 
5231  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5232  Consumer.addKeywordResult("using");
5233 
5234  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
5235  Consumer.addKeywordResult("static_assert");
5236  }
5237  }
5238 }
5239 
5240 std::unique_ptr<TypoCorrectionConsumer> Sema::makeTypoCorrectionConsumer(
5241  const DeclarationNameInfo &TypoName, Sema::LookupNameKind LookupKind,
5242  Scope *S, CXXScopeSpec *SS, CorrectionCandidateCallback &CCC,
5243  DeclContext *MemberContext, bool EnteringContext,
5244  const ObjCObjectPointerType *OPT, bool ErrorRecovery) {
5245 
5246  if (Diags.hasFatalErrorOccurred() || !getLangOpts().SpellChecking ||
5247  DisableTypoCorrection)
5248  return nullptr;
5249 
5250  // In Microsoft mode, don't perform typo correction in a template member
5251  // function dependent context because it interferes with the "lookup into
5252  // dependent bases of class templates" feature.
5253  if (getLangOpts().MSVCCompat && CurContext->isDependentContext() &&
5254  isa<CXXMethodDecl>(CurContext))
5255  return nullptr;
5256 
5257  // We only attempt to correct typos for identifiers.
5258  IdentifierInfo *Typo = TypoName.getName().getAsIdentifierInfo();
5259  if (!Typo)
5260  return nullptr;
5261 
5262  // If the scope specifier itself was invalid, don't try to correct
5263  // typos.
5264  if (SS && SS->isInvalid())
5265  return nullptr;
5266 
5267  // Never try to correct typos during any kind of code synthesis.
5268  if (!CodeSynthesisContexts.empty())
5269  return nullptr;
5270 
5271  // Don't try to correct 'super'.
5272  if (S && S->isInObjcMethodScope() && Typo == getSuperIdentifier())
5273  return nullptr;
5274 
5275  // Abort if typo correction already failed for this specific typo.
5276  IdentifierSourceLocations::iterator locs = TypoCorrectionFailures.find(Typo);
5277  if (locs != TypoCorrectionFailures.end() &&
5278  locs->second.count(TypoName.getLoc()))
5279  return nullptr;
5280 
5281  // Don't try to correct the identifier "vector" when in AltiVec mode.
5282  // TODO: Figure out why typo correction misbehaves in this case, fix it, and
5283  // remove this workaround.
5284  if ((getLangOpts().AltiVec || getLangOpts().ZVector) && Typo->isStr("vector"))
5285  return nullptr;
5286 
5287  // Provide a stop gap for files that are just seriously broken. Trying
5288  // to correct all typos can turn into a HUGE performance penalty, causing
5289  // some files to take minutes to get rejected by the parser.
5290  unsigned Limit = getDiagnostics().getDiagnosticOptions().SpellCheckingLimit;
5291  if (Limit && TyposCorrected >= Limit)
5292  return nullptr;
5293  ++TyposCorrected;
5294 
5295  // If we're handling a missing symbol error, using modules, and the
5296  // special search all modules option is used, look for a missing import.
5297  if (ErrorRecovery && getLangOpts().Modules &&
5298  getLangOpts().ModulesSearchAll) {
5299  // The following has the side effect of loading the missing module.
5300  getModuleLoader().lookupMissingImports(Typo->getName(),
5301  TypoName.getBeginLoc());
5302  }
5303 
5304  // Extend the lifetime of the callback. We delayed this until here
5305  // to avoid allocations in the hot path (which is where no typo correction
5306  // occurs). Note that CorrectionCandidateCallback is polymorphic and
5307  // initially stack-allocated.
5308  std::unique_ptr<CorrectionCandidateCallback> ClonedCCC = CCC.clone();
5309  auto Consumer = std::make_unique<TypoCorrectionConsumer>(
5310  *this, TypoName, LookupKind, S, SS, std::move(ClonedCCC), MemberContext,
5311  EnteringContext);
5312 
5313  // Perform name lookup to find visible, similarly-named entities.
5314  bool IsUnqualifiedLookup = false;
5315  DeclContext *QualifiedDC = MemberContext;
5316  if (MemberContext) {
5317  LookupVisibleDecls(MemberContext, LookupKind, *Consumer);
5318 
5319  // Look in qualified interfaces.
5320  if (OPT) {
5321  for (auto *I : OPT->quals())
5322  LookupVisibleDecls(I, LookupKind, *Consumer);
5323  }
5324  } else if (SS && SS->isSet()) {
5325  QualifiedDC = computeDeclContext(*SS, EnteringContext);
5326  if (!QualifiedDC)
5327  return nullptr;
5328 
5329  LookupVisibleDecls(QualifiedDC, LookupKind, *Consumer);
5330  } else {
5331  IsUnqualifiedLookup = true;
5332  }
5333 
5334  // Determine whether we are going to search in the various namespaces for
5335  // corrections.
5336  bool SearchNamespaces
5337  = getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
5338  (IsUnqualifiedLookup || (SS && SS->isSet()));
5339 
5340  if (IsUnqualifiedLookup || SearchNamespaces) {
5341  // For unqualified lookup, look through all of the names that we have
5342  // seen in this translation unit.
5343  // FIXME: Re-add the ability to skip very unlikely potential corrections.
5344  for (const auto &I : Context.Idents)
5345  Consumer->FoundName(I.getKey());
5346 
5347  // Walk through identifiers in external identifier sources.
5348  // FIXME: Re-add the ability to skip very unlikely potential corrections.
5349  if (IdentifierInfoLookup *External
5350  = Context.Idents.getExternalIdentifierLookup()) {
5351  std::unique_ptr<IdentifierIterator> Iter(External->getIdentifiers());
5352  do {
5353  StringRef Name = Iter->Next();
5354  if (Name.empty())
5355  break;
5356 
5357  Consumer->FoundName(Name);
5358  } while (true);
5359  }
5360  }
5361 
5362  AddKeywordsToConsumer(*this, *Consumer, S,
5363  *Consumer->getCorrectionValidator(),
5364  SS && SS->isNotEmpty());
5365 
5366  // Build the NestedNameSpecifiers for the KnownNamespaces, if we're going
5367  // to search those namespaces.
5368  if (SearchNamespaces) {
5369  // Load any externally-known namespaces.
5370  if (ExternalSource && !LoadedExternalKnownNamespaces) {
5371  SmallVector<NamespaceDecl *, 4> ExternalKnownNamespaces;
5372  LoadedExternalKnownNamespaces = true;
5373  ExternalSource->ReadKnownNamespaces(ExternalKnownNamespaces);
5374  for (auto *N : ExternalKnownNamespaces)
5375  KnownNamespaces[N] = true;
5376  }
5377 
5378  Consumer->addNamespaces(KnownNamespaces);
5379  }
5380 
5381  return Consumer;
5382 }
5383 
5384 /// Try to "correct" a typo in the source code by finding
5385 /// visible declarations whose names are similar to the name that was
5386 /// present in the source code.
5387 ///
5388 /// \param TypoName the \c DeclarationNameInfo structure that contains
5389 /// the name that was present in the source code along with its location.
5390 ///
5391 /// \param LookupKind the name-lookup criteria used to search for the name.
5392 ///
5393 /// \param S the scope in which name lookup occurs.
5394 ///
5395 /// \param SS the nested-name-specifier that precedes the name we're
5396 /// looking for, if present.
5397 ///
5398 /// \param CCC A CorrectionCandidateCallback object that provides further
5399 /// validation of typo correction candidates. It also provides flags for
5400 /// determining the set of keywords permitted.
5401 ///
5402 /// \param MemberContext if non-NULL, the context in which to look for
5403 /// a member access expression.
5404 ///
5405 /// \param EnteringContext whether we're entering the context described by
5406 /// the nested-name-specifier SS.
5407 ///
5408 /// \param OPT when non-NULL, the search for visible declarations will
5409 /// also walk the protocols in the qualified interfaces of \p OPT.
5410 ///
5411 /// \returns a \c TypoCorrection containing the corrected name if the typo
5412 /// along with information such as the \c NamedDecl where the corrected name
5413 /// was declared, and any additional \c NestedNameSpecifier needed to access
5414 /// it (C++ only). The \c TypoCorrection is empty if there is no correction.
5415 TypoCorrection Sema::CorrectTypo(const DeclarationNameInfo &TypoName,
5416  Sema::LookupNameKind LookupKind,
5417  Scope *S, CXXScopeSpec *SS,
5418  CorrectionCandidateCallback &CCC,
5419  CorrectTypoKind Mode,
5420  DeclContext *MemberContext,
5421  bool EnteringContext,
5422  const ObjCObjectPointerType *OPT,
5423  bool RecordFailure) {
5424  // Always let the ExternalSource have the first chance at correction, even
5425  // if we would otherwise have given up.
5426  if (ExternalSource) {
5427  if (TypoCorrection Correction =
5428  ExternalSource->CorrectTypo(TypoName, LookupKind, S, SS, CCC,
5429  MemberContext, EnteringContext, OPT))
5430  return Correction;
5431  }
5432 
5433  // Ugly hack equivalent to CTC == CTC_ObjCMessageReceiver;
5434  // WantObjCSuper is only true for CTC_ObjCMessageReceiver and for
5435  // some instances of CTC_Unknown, while WantRemainingKeywords is true
5436  // for CTC_Unknown but not for CTC_ObjCMessageReceiver.
5437  bool ObjCMessageReceiver = CCC.WantObjCSuper && !CCC.WantRemainingKeywords;
5438 
5439  IdentifierInfo *Typo = TypoName.getName().getAsIdentifierInfo();
5440  auto Consumer = makeTypoCorrectionConsumer(TypoName, LookupKind, S, SS, CCC,
5441  MemberContext, EnteringContext,
5442  OPT, Mode == CTK_ErrorRecovery);
5443 
5444  if (!Consumer)
5445  return TypoCorrection();
5446 
5447  // If we haven't found anything, we're done.
5448  if (Consumer->empty())
5449  return FailedCorrection(Typo, TypoName.getLoc(), RecordFailure);
5450 
5451  // Make sure the best edit distance (prior to adding any namespace qualifiers)
5452  // is not more that about a third of the length of the typo's identifier.
5453  unsigned ED = Consumer->getBestEditDistance(true);
5454  unsigned TypoLen = Typo->getName().size();
5455  if (ED > 0 && TypoLen / ED < 3)
5456  return FailedCorrection(Typo, TypoName.getLoc(), RecordFailure);
5457 
5458  TypoCorrection BestTC = Consumer->getNextCorrection();
5459  TypoCorrection SecondBestTC = Consumer->getNextCorrection();
5460  if (!BestTC)
5461  return FailedCorrection(Typo, TypoName.getLoc(), RecordFailure);
5462 
5463  ED = BestTC.getEditDistance();
5464 
5465  if (TypoLen >= 3 && ED > 0 && TypoLen / ED < 3) {
5466  // If this was an unqualified lookup and we believe the callback
5467  // object wouldn't have filtered out possible corrections, note
5468  // that no correction was found.
5469  return FailedCorrection(Typo, TypoName.getLoc(), RecordFailure);
5470  }
5471 
5472  // If only a single name remains, return that result.
5473  if (!SecondBestTC ||
5474  SecondBestTC.getEditDistance(false) > BestTC.getEditDistance(false)) {
5475  const TypoCorrection &Result = BestTC;
5476 
5477  // Don't correct to a keyword that's the same as the typo; the keyword
5478  // wasn't actually in scope.
5479  if (ED == 0 && Result.isKeyword())
5480  return FailedCorrection(Typo, TypoName.getLoc(), RecordFailure);
5481 
5482  TypoCorrection TC = Result;
5483  TC.setCorrectionRange(SS, TypoName);
5484  checkCorrectionVisibility(*this, TC);
5485  return TC;
5486  } else if (SecondBestTC && ObjCMessageReceiver) {
5487  // Prefer 'super' when we're completing in a message-receiver
5488  // context.
5489 
5490  if (BestTC.getCorrection().getAsString() != "super") {
5491  if (SecondBestTC.getCorrection().getAsString() == "super")
5492  BestTC = SecondBestTC;
5493  else if ((*Consumer)["super"].front().isKeyword())
5494  BestTC = (*Consumer)["super"].front();
5495  }
5496  // Don't correct to a keyword that's the same as the typo; the keyword
5497  // wasn't actually in scope.
5498  if (BestTC.getEditDistance() == 0 ||
5499  BestTC.getCorrection().getAsString() != "super")
5500  return FailedCorrection(Typo, TypoName.getLoc(), RecordFailure);
5501 
5502  BestTC.setCorrectionRange(SS, TypoName);
5503  return BestTC;
5504  }
5505 
5506  // Record the failure's location if needed and return an empty correction. If
5507  // this was an unqualified lookup and we believe the callback object did not
5508  // filter out possible corrections, also cache the failure for the typo.
5509  return FailedCorrection(Typo, TypoName.getLoc(), RecordFailure && !SecondBestTC);
5510 }
5511 
5512 /// Try to "correct" a typo in the source code by finding
5513 /// visible declarations whose names are similar to the name that was
5514 /// present in the source code.
5515 ///
5516 /// \param TypoName the \c DeclarationNameInfo structure that contains
5517 /// the name that was present in the source code along with its location.
5518 ///
5519 /// \param LookupKind the name-lookup criteria used to search for the name.
5520 ///
5521 /// \param S the scope in which name lookup occurs.
5522 ///
5523 /// \param SS the nested-name-specifier that precedes the name we're
5524 /// looking for, if present.
5525 ///
5526 /// \param CCC A CorrectionCandidateCallback object that provides further
5527 /// validation of typo correction candidates. It also provides flags for
5528 /// determining the set of keywords permitted.
5529 ///
5530 /// \param TDG A TypoDiagnosticGenerator functor that will be used to print
5531 /// diagnostics when the actual typo correction is attempted.
5532 ///
5533 /// \param TRC A TypoRecoveryCallback functor that will be used to build an
5534 /// Expr from a typo correction candidate.
5535 ///
5536 /// \param MemberContext if non-NULL, the context in which to look for
5537 /// a member access expression.
5538 ///
5539 /// \param EnteringContext whether we're entering the context described by
5540 /// the nested-name-specifier SS.
5541 ///
5542 /// \param OPT when non-NULL, the search for visible declarations will
5543 /// also walk the protocols in the qualified interfaces of \p OPT.
5544 ///
5545 /// \returns a new \c TypoExpr that will later be replaced in the AST with an
5546 /// Expr representing the result of performing typo correction, or nullptr if
5547 /// typo correction is not possible. If nullptr is returned, no diagnostics will
5548 /// be emitted and it is the responsibility of the caller to emit any that are
5549 /// needed.
5550 TypoExpr *Sema::CorrectTypoDelayed(
5551  const DeclarationNameInfo &TypoName, Sema::LookupNameKind LookupKind,
5552  Scope *S, CXXScopeSpec *SS, CorrectionCandidateCallback &CCC,
5553  TypoDiagnosticGenerator TDG, TypoRecoveryCallback TRC, CorrectTypoKind Mode,
5554  DeclContext *MemberContext, bool EnteringContext,
5555  const ObjCObjectPointerType *OPT) {
5556  auto Consumer = makeTypoCorrectionConsumer(TypoName, LookupKind, S, SS, CCC,
5557  MemberContext, EnteringContext,
5558  OPT, Mode == CTK_ErrorRecovery);
5559 
5560  // Give the external sema source a chance to correct the typo.
5561  TypoCorrection ExternalTypo;
5562  if (ExternalSource && Consumer) {
5563  ExternalTypo = ExternalSource->CorrectTypo(
5564  TypoName, LookupKind, S, SS, *Consumer->getCorrectionValidator(),
5565  MemberContext, EnteringContext, OPT);
5566  if (ExternalTypo)
5567  Consumer->addCorrection(ExternalTypo);
5568  }
5569 
5570  if (!Consumer || Consumer->empty())
5571  return nullptr;
5572 
5573  // Make sure the best edit distance (prior to adding any namespace qualifiers)
5574  // is not more that about a third of the length of the typo's identifier.
5575  unsigned ED = Consumer->getBestEditDistance(true);
5576  IdentifierInfo *Typo = TypoName.getName().getAsIdentifierInfo();
5577  if (!ExternalTypo && ED > 0 && Typo->getName().size() / ED < 3)
5578  return nullptr;
5579  ExprEvalContexts.back().NumTypos++;
5580  return createDelayedTypo(std::move(Consumer), std::move(TDG), std::move(TRC),
5581  TypoName.getLoc());
5582 }
5583 
5584 void TypoCorrection::addCorrectionDecl(NamedDecl *CDecl) {
5585  if (!CDecl) return;
5586 
5587  if (isKeyword())
5588  CorrectionDecls.clear();
5589 
5590  CorrectionDecls.push_back(CDecl);
5591 
5592  if (!CorrectionName)
5593  CorrectionName = CDecl->getDeclName();
5594 }
5595 
5596 std::string TypoCorrection::getAsString(const LangOptions &LO) const {
5597  if (CorrectionNameSpec) {
5598  std::string tmpBuffer;
5599  llvm::raw_string_ostream PrefixOStream(tmpBuffer);
5600  CorrectionNameSpec->print(PrefixOStream, PrintingPolicy(LO));
5601  PrefixOStream << CorrectionName;
5602  return PrefixOStream.str();
5603  }
5604 
5605  return CorrectionName.getAsString();
5606 }
5607 
5608 bool CorrectionCandidateCallback::ValidateCandidate(
5609  const TypoCorrection &candidate) {
5610  if (!candidate.isResolved())
5611  return true;
5612 
5613  if (candidate.isKeyword())
5614  return WantTypeSpecifiers || WantExpressionKeywords || WantCXXNamedCasts ||
5615  WantRemainingKeywords || WantObjCSuper;
5616 
5617  bool HasNonType = false;
5618  bool HasStaticMethod = false;
5619  bool HasNonStaticMethod = false;
5620  for (Decl *D : candidate) {
5621  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FTD = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D))
5622  D = FTD->getTemplatedDecl();
5623  if (CXXMethodDecl *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D)) {
5624  if (Method->isStatic())
5625  HasStaticMethod = true;
5626  else
5627  HasNonStaticMethod = true;
5628  }
5629  if (!isa<TypeDecl>(D))
5630  HasNonType = true;
5631  }
5632 
5633  if (IsAddressOfOperand && HasNonStaticMethod && !HasStaticMethod &&
5634  !candidate.getCorrectionSpecifier())
5635  return false;
5636 
5637  return WantTypeSpecifiers || HasNonType;
5638 }
5639 
5640 FunctionCallFilterCCC::FunctionCallFilterCCC(Sema &SemaRef, unsigned NumArgs,
5641  bool HasExplicitTemplateArgs,
5642  MemberExpr *ME)
5643  : NumArgs(NumArgs), HasExplicitTemplateArgs(HasExplicitTemplateArgs),
5644  CurContext(SemaRef.CurContext), MemberFn(ME) {
5645  WantTypeSpecifiers = false;
5646  WantFunctionLikeCasts = SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
5647  !HasExplicitTemplateArgs && NumArgs == 1;
5648  WantCXXNamedCasts = HasExplicitTemplateArgs && NumArgs == 1;
5649  WantRemainingKeywords = false;
5650 }
5651 
5652 bool FunctionCallFilterCCC::ValidateCandidate(const TypoCorrection &candidate) {
5653  if (!candidate.getCorrectionDecl())
5654  return candidate.isKeyword();
5655 
5656  for (auto *C : candidate) {
5657  FunctionDecl *FD = nullptr;
5658  NamedDecl *ND = C->getUnderlyingDecl();
5659  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FTD = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(ND))
5660  FD = FTD->getTemplatedDecl();
5661  if (!HasExplicitTemplateArgs && !FD) {
5662  if (!(FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ND)) && isa<ValueDecl>(ND)) {
5663  // If the Decl is neither a function nor a template function,
5664  // determine if it is a pointer or reference to a function. If so,
5665  // check against the number of arguments expected for the pointee.
5666  QualType ValType = cast<ValueDecl>(ND)->getType();
5667  if (ValType.isNull())
5668  continue;
5669  if (ValType->isAnyPointerType() || ValType->isReferenceType())
5670  ValType = ValType->getPointeeType();
5671  if (const FunctionProtoType *FPT = ValType->getAs<FunctionProtoType>())
5672  if (FPT->getNumParams() == NumArgs)
5673  return true;
5674  }
5675  }
5676 
5677  // A typo for a function-style cast can look like a function call in C++.
5678  if ((HasExplicitTemplateArgs ? getAsTypeTemplateDecl(ND) != nullptr
5679  : isa<TypeDecl>(ND)) &&
5680  CurContext->getParentASTContext().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
5681  // Only a class or class template can take two or more arguments.
5682  return NumArgs <= 1 || HasExplicitTemplateArgs || isa<CXXRecordDecl>(ND);
5683 
5684  // Skip the current candidate if it is not a FunctionDecl or does not accept
5685  // the current number of arguments.
5686  if (!FD || !(FD->getNumParams() >= NumArgs &&
5687  FD->getMinRequiredArguments() <= NumArgs))
5688  continue;
5689 
5690  // If the current candidate is a non-static C++ method, skip the candidate
5691  // unless the method being corrected--or the current DeclContext, if the
5692  // function being corrected is not a method--is a method in the same class
5693  // or a descendent class of the candidate's parent class.
5694  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)) {
5695  if (MemberFn || !MD->isStatic()) {
5696  const auto *CurMD =
5697  MemberFn
5698  ? dyn_cast_if_present<CXXMethodDecl>(MemberFn->getMemberDecl())
5699  : dyn_cast_if_present<CXXMethodDecl>(CurContext);
5700  const CXXRecordDecl *CurRD =
5701  CurMD ? CurMD->getParent()->getCanonicalDecl() : nullptr;
5702  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = MD->getParent()->getCanonicalDecl();
5703  if (!CurRD || (CurRD != RD && !CurRD->isDerivedFrom(RD)))
5704  continue;
5705  }
5706  }
5707  return true;
5708  }
5709  return false;
5710 }
5711 
5712 void Sema::diagnoseTypo(const TypoCorrection &Correction,
5713  const PartialDiagnostic &TypoDiag,
5714  bool ErrorRecovery) {
5715  diagnoseTypo(Correction, TypoDiag, PDiag(diag::note_previous_decl),
5716  ErrorRecovery);
5717 }
5718 
5719 /// Find which declaration we should import to provide the definition of
5720 /// the given declaration.
5721 static const NamedDecl *getDefinitionToImport(const NamedDecl *D) {
5722  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
5723  return VD->getDefinition();
5724  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
5725  return FD->getDefinition();
5726  if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(D))
5727  return TD->getDefinition();
5728  if (const auto *ID = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(D))
5729  return ID->getDefinition();
5730  if (const auto *PD = dyn_cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(D))
5731  return PD->getDefinition();
5732  if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TemplateDecl>(D))
5733  if (const NamedDecl *TTD = TD->getTemplatedDecl())
5734  return getDefinitionToImport(TTD);
5735  return nullptr;
5736 }
5737 
5738 void Sema::diagnoseMissingImport(SourceLocation Loc, const NamedDecl *Decl,
5739  MissingImportKind MIK, bool Recover) {
5740  // Suggest importing a module providing the definition of this entity, if
5741  // possible.
5742  const NamedDecl *Def = getDefinitionToImport(Decl);
5743  if (!Def)
5744  Def = Decl;
5745 
5746  Module *Owner = getOwningModule(Def);
5747  assert(Owner && "definition of hidden declaration is not in a module");
5748 
5749  llvm::SmallVector<Module*, 8> OwningModules;
5750  OwningModules.push_back(Owner);
5751  auto Merged = Context.getModulesWithMergedDefinition(Def);
5752  OwningModules.insert(OwningModules.end(), Merged.begin(), Merged.end());
5753 
5754  diagnoseMissingImport(Loc, Def, Def->getLocation(), OwningModules, MIK,
5755  Recover);
5756 }
5757 
5758 /// Get a "quoted.h" or <angled.h> include path to use in a diagnostic
5759 /// suggesting the addition of a #include of the specified file.
5760 static std::string getHeaderNameForHeader(Preprocessor &PP, FileEntryRef E,
5761  llvm::StringRef IncludingFile) {
5762  bool IsAngled = false;
5763  auto Path = PP.getHeaderSearchInfo().suggestPathToFileForDiagnostics(
5764  E, IncludingFile, &IsAngled);
5765  return (IsAngled ? '<' : '"') + Path + (IsAngled ? '>' : '"');
5766 }
5767 
5768 void Sema::diagnoseMissingImport(SourceLocation UseLoc, const NamedDecl *Decl,
5769  SourceLocation DeclLoc,
5770  ArrayRef<Module *> Modules,
5771  MissingImportKind MIK, bool Recover) {
5772  assert(!Modules.empty());
5773 
5774  // See https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/73893. It is generally
5775  // confusing than helpful to show the namespace is not visible.
5776  if (isa<NamespaceDecl>(Decl))
5777  return;
5778 
5779  auto NotePrevious = [&] {
5780  // FIXME: Suppress the note backtrace even under
5781  // -fdiagnostics-show-note-include-stack. We don't care how this
5782  // declaration was previously reached.
5783  Diag(DeclLoc, diag::note_unreachable_entity) << (int)MIK;
5784  };
5785 
5786  // Weed out duplicates from module list.
5787  llvm::SmallVector<Module*, 8> UniqueModules;
5788  llvm::SmallDenseSet<Module*, 8> UniqueModuleSet;
5789  for (auto *M : Modules) {
5790  if (M->isExplicitGlobalModule() || M->isPrivateModule())
5791  continue;
5792  if (UniqueModuleSet.insert(M).second)
5793  UniqueModules.push_back(M);
5794  }
5795 
5796  // Try to find a suitable header-name to #include.
5797  std::string HeaderName;
5798  if (OptionalFileEntryRef Header =
5799  PP.getHeaderToIncludeForDiagnostics(UseLoc, DeclLoc)) {
5800  if (const FileEntry *FE =
5801  SourceMgr.getFileEntryForID(SourceMgr.getFileID(UseLoc)))
5802  HeaderName =
5803  getHeaderNameForHeader(PP, *Header, FE->tryGetRealPathName());
5804  }
5805 
5806  // If we have a #include we should suggest, or if all definition locations
5807  // were in global module fragments, don't suggest an import.
5808  if (!HeaderName.empty() || UniqueModules.empty()) {
5809  // FIXME: Find a smart place to suggest inserting a #include, and add
5810  // a FixItHint there.
5811  Diag(UseLoc, diag::err_module_unimported_use_header)
5812  << (int)MIK << Decl << !HeaderName.empty() << HeaderName;
5813  // Produce a note showing where the entity was declared.
5814  NotePrevious();
5815  if (Recover)
5816  createImplicitModuleImportForErrorRecovery(UseLoc, Modules[0]);
5817  return;
5818  }
5819 
5820  Modules = UniqueModules;
5821 
5822  auto GetModuleNameForDiagnostic = [this](const Module *M) -> std::string {
5823  if (M->isModuleMapModule())
5824  return M->getFullModuleName();
5825 
5826  Module *CurrentModule = getCurrentModule();
5827 
5828  if (M->isImplicitGlobalModule())
5829  M = M->getTopLevelModule();
5830 
5831  bool IsInTheSameModule =
5832  CurrentModule && CurrentModule->getPrimaryModuleInterfaceName() ==
5833  M->getPrimaryModuleInterfaceName();
5834 
5835  // If the current module unit is in the same module with M, it is OK to show
5836  // the partition name. Otherwise, it'll be sufficient to show the primary
5837  // module name.
5838  if (IsInTheSameModule)
5839  return M->getTopLevelModuleName().str();
5840  else
5841  return M->getPrimaryModuleInterfaceName().str();
5842  };
5843 
5844  if (Modules.size() > 1) {
5845  std::string ModuleList;
5846  unsigned N = 0;
5847  for (const auto *M : Modules) {
5848  ModuleList += "\n ";
5849  if (++N == 5 && N != Modules.size()) {
5850  ModuleList += "[...]";
5851  break;
5852  }
5853  ModuleList += GetModuleNameForDiagnostic(M);
5854  }
5855 
5856  Diag(UseLoc, diag::err_module_unimported_use_multiple)
5857  << (int)MIK << Decl << ModuleList;
5858  } else {
5859  // FIXME: Add a FixItHint that imports the corresponding module.
5860  Diag(UseLoc, diag::err_module_unimported_use)
5861  << (int)MIK << Decl << GetModuleNameForDiagnostic(Modules[0]);
5862  }
5863 
5864  NotePrevious();
5865 
5866  // Try to recover by implicitly importing this module.
5867  if (Recover)
5868  createImplicitModuleImportForErrorRecovery(UseLoc, Modules[0]);
5869 }
5870 
5871 /// Diagnose a successfully-corrected typo. Separated from the correction
5872 /// itself to allow external validation of the result, etc.
5873 ///
5874 /// \param Correction The result of performing typo correction.
5875 /// \param TypoDiag The diagnostic to produce. This will have the corrected
5876 /// string added to it (and usually also a fixit).
5877 /// \param PrevNote A note to use when indicating the location of the entity to
5878 /// which we are correcting. Will have the correction string added to it.
5879 /// \param ErrorRecovery If \c true (the default), the caller is going to
5880 /// recover from the typo as if the corrected string had been typed.
5881 /// In this case, \c PDiag must be an error, and we will attach a fixit
5882 /// to it.
5883 void Sema::diagnoseTypo(const TypoCorrection &Correction,
5884  const PartialDiagnostic &TypoDiag,
5885  const PartialDiagnostic &PrevNote,
5886  bool ErrorRecovery) {
5887  std::string CorrectedStr = Correction.getAsString(getLangOpts());
5888  std::string CorrectedQuotedStr = Correction.getQuoted(getLangOpts());
5889  FixItHint FixTypo = FixItHint::CreateReplacement(
5890  Correction.getCorrectionRange(), CorrectedStr);
5891 
5892  // Maybe we're just missing a module import.
5893  if (Correction.requiresImport()) {
5894  NamedDecl *Decl = Correction.getFoundDecl();
5895  assert(Decl && "import required but no declaration to import");
5896 
5897  diagnoseMissingImport(Correction.getCorrectionRange().getBegin(), Decl,
5898  MissingImportKind::Declaration, ErrorRecovery);
5899  return;
5900  }
5901 
5902  Diag(Correction.getCorrectionRange().getBegin(), TypoDiag)
5903  << CorrectedQuotedStr << (ErrorRecovery ? FixTypo : FixItHint());
5904 
5905  NamedDecl *ChosenDecl =
5906  Correction.isKeyword() ? nullptr : Correction.getFoundDecl();
5907  if (PrevNote.getDiagID() && ChosenDecl)
5908  Diag(ChosenDecl->getLocation(), PrevNote)
5909  << CorrectedQuotedStr << (ErrorRecovery ? FixItHint() : FixTypo);
5910 
5911  // Add any extra diagnostics.
5912  for (const PartialDiagnostic &PD : Correction.getExtraDiagnostics())
5913  Diag(Correction.getCorrectionRange().getBegin(), PD);
5914 }
5915 
5916 TypoExpr *Sema::createDelayedTypo(std::unique_ptr<TypoCorrectionConsumer> TCC,
5917  TypoDiagnosticGenerator TDG,
5918  TypoRecoveryCallback TRC,
5919  SourceLocation TypoLoc) {
5920  assert(TCC && "createDelayedTypo requires a valid TypoCorrectionConsumer");
5921  auto TE = new (Context) TypoExpr(Context.DependentTy, TypoLoc);
5922  auto &State = DelayedTypos[TE];
5923  State.Consumer = std::move(TCC);
5924  State.DiagHandler = std::move(TDG);
5925  State.RecoveryHandler = std::move(TRC);
5926  if (TE)
5927  TypoExprs.push_back(TE);
5928  return TE;
5929 }
5930 
5931 const Sema::TypoExprState &Sema::getTypoExprState(TypoExpr *TE) const {
5932  auto Entry = DelayedTypos.find(TE);
5933  assert(Entry != DelayedTypos.end() &&
5934  "Failed to get the state for a TypoExpr!");
5935  return Entry->second;
5936 }
5937 
5938 void Sema::clearDelayedTypo(TypoExpr *TE) {
5939  DelayedTypos.erase(TE);
5940 }

5942 void Sema::ActOnPragmaDump(Scope *S, SourceLocation IILoc, IdentifierInfo *II) {
5943  DeclarationNameInfo Name(II, IILoc);
5944  LookupResult R(*this, Name, LookupAnyName,
5945  RedeclarationKind::NotForRedeclaration);
5946  R.suppressDiagnostics();
5947  R.setHideTags(false);
5948  LookupName(R, S);
5949  R.dump();
5950 }

5952 void Sema::ActOnPragmaDump(Expr *E) {

5954 }
5955 
5956 RedeclarationKind Sema::forRedeclarationInCurContext() const {
5957  // A declaration with an owning module for linkage can never link against
5958  // anything that is not visible. We don't need to check linkage here; if
5959  // the context has internal linkage, redeclaration lookup won't find things
5960  // from other TUs, and we can't safely compute linkage yet in general.
5961  if (cast<Decl>(CurContext)->getOwningModuleForLinkage(/*IgnoreLinkage*/ true))
5962  return RedeclarationKind::ForVisibleRedeclaration;
5963  return RedeclarationKind::ForExternalRedeclaration;
5964 }
